eted-continue\"],\n    \"generation\": 1,\n    \"continuedFromRun\": null\n  },\n  \"reducer\": {\n    \"enabled\": true,\n    \"version\": \"1.0\",\n    \"registryFile\": \"deep-research-findings-registry.json\",\n    \"dashboardFile\": \"deep-research-dashboard.md\",\n    \"strategyFile\": \"deep-research-strategy.md\",\n    \"machineOwnedSections\": [\n      \"key-questions\",\n      \"answered-questions\",\n      \"what-worked\",\n      \"what-failed\",\n      \"exhausted-approaches\",\n      \"ruled-out-directions\",\n      \"next-focus\"\n    ]\n  },\n  \"capabilityMatrixPath\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/runtime_capabilities.json\",\n  \"capabilityMatrixDocPath\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/capability_matrix.md\",\n  \"runtimeCapabilityResolver\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs\",\n  \"reducerScriptPath\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs\",\n  \"pauseSentinelPath\": \".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-9/.deep-research-pause\",\n  \"archiveRoot\": \".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-9/_archive\",\n  \"migrationWindowDays\": 28,\n  \"fileProtection\": {\n    \"deep-research-config.json\": \"immutable\",\n    \"deep-research-state.jsonl\": \"append-only\",\n    \"deep-research-strategy.md\": \"mutable\",\n    \"deep-research-dashboard.md\": \"auto-generated\",\n    \"deep-research-findings-registry.json\": \"auto-generated\",\n    \"iteration-*.md\": \"write-once\",\n    \"research.md\": \"mutable\",\n    \"resource-map.md\": \"mutable\"\n  },\n  \"config\": {\n    \"fanout_lineage_artifact_dir\": \".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-9\",\n    \"stopPolicy\": \"convergence\"\n  }\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":81,"totalLines":81,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-9/deep-research-config.json","time":{"start":1783488683287,"end":1783488683298}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09a7e4a4727c6b9b016a4de0ab3b7c8191bc98cc2972d81c74"}},"id":"prt_f40359d13001GViLEnojqi0fUr","sessionID":"ses_0bfcc9e59ffevWtcj5ONdHm47k","messageID":"msg_f40356803001Qmcw3hHWrmyEU2"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783488683301,"sessionID":"ses_0bfcc9e59ffevWtcj5ONdHm47k","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_646wk9fwKVMELUTPLcCfFZ4E","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-9/deep-research-strategy.md","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-9/deep-research-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deep Research Strategy - gpt55-fast-9\n2: \n3: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n4: \n5: This detached fan-out lineage validates the proposed deep-loop unification design using the bound artifact directory as the state boundary.\n6: \n7: ## 2. TOPIC\n8: \n9: Validate and stress-test the merge design for folding deep-loop-runtime into deep-loop-workflows as system-deep-loop: structural layout, bidirectional path-coupling repair, the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow, reference migration across commands/agents/READMEs/advisor-corpus, and whether fallback-router.ts should be wired for real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback.\n10: \n11: <!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n12: ## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n13: \n14: - [x] Is the proposed `system-deep-loop/` layout with nested `runtime/` structurally coherent without creating duplicate skill identity or mode ambiguity?\n15: - [x] Are the bidirectional path-coupling repair rules complete for workflow-to-runtime and runtime-to-workflow references after the move?\n16: - [x] Is the `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow repair complete, including hidden runtime seams and tests beyond the obvious package and tsconfig files?\n17: - [ ] What command, agent, README, graph metadata, advisor-corpus, and model-prompt references must migrate, and which should intentionally remain stable?\n18: - [ ] Should `fallback-router.ts` be wired now for GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback, or remain deferred/manual for this research phase?\n19: <!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n20: \n21: ## 4. NON-GOALS\n22: \n23: - Do not modify `deep-loop-workflows`, `deep-loop-runtime`, command assets, agents, advisor corpora, specs, or READMEs outside this lineage.\n24: - Do not execute the merge or implement fallback routing.\n25: - Do not write outside `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-9`.\n26: \n27: ## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n28: \n29: - Stop after legal convergence once all five key questions have evidence-backed answers and at least 3 iterations have completed.\n30: - Stop at `maxIterations: 10` if convergence does not arrive earlier.\n31: - Continue past a low-novelty STOP candidate if quality guards lack source diversity or question coverage.\n32: \n33: <!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n34: ## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n35: \n36: - [x] Structural layout: coherent if `system-deep-loop` is the single public hub and `runtime/` is backend infrastructure with no routable skill identity or mode metadata (iteration 1; evidence: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:12`, `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:14-17`, `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:64-67`).\n37: - [x] Path-coupling: Class A and Class B repair directions are correct, but child 002's file table is incomplete; add research/review runtime-capability shims, council orchestrate-session, council replay graph, and a classified runtime-test inventory (iteration 2; evidence: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/orchestrate-session.cjs:16-18`, `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs:21-66`, `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/runtime-capabilities.vitest.ts:10-12`).\n38: - [x] Tooling-borrow: the four planned compiler/test edits are necessary but incomplete; phase 002 should also cover runtime `artifact-root.cjs`, its test, and `test:council` anchor fixture paths if those gates run before child 003 (iteration 3; evidence: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs:16-19`, `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/artifact-root.vitest.ts:10-25`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/council-playbook-anchor-integrity.vitest.ts:7-67`).\n39: <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n40: \n41: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n42: <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n43: ## 7. WHAT WORKED\n44: \n45: - Paired hub/runtime contract reads: verified the public hub plus frozen backend split and the one-graph-metadata invariant (iteration 1).\n46: - Executable grep plus targeted reads: found omitted reverse-coupling files and separated imports from prose hits (iteration 2).\n47: - Validation-gate tracing: starting from the named `test:council` and runtime gates exposed hidden path-sensitive seams (iteration 3).\n48: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n49: \n50: <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n51: ## 8. WHAT FAILED\n52: \n53: - Code graph status: stale and scope-excluding commands/agents/specs, so it was not used as proof for structural claims (iteration 1).\n54: - Broad workflow markdown grep: too noisy for actionable path-coupling classification due to playbooks, changelogs, feature catalogs, and benchmark outputs (iteration 2).\n55: - Whole-system-spec-kit grep: useful for future child 003 inventory, but too broad for phase 002 blocker classification without gate ownership buckets (iteration 3).\n56: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n57: \n58: <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n59: ## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n60: \n61: - Flattening workflow packets and runtime libraries into one directory: contradicts per-mode contract ownership and risks mode ambiguity (iteration 1, evidence: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:64-67`).\n62: - Keeping `runtime/SKILL.md` discoverable after the merge: contradicts runtime's non-user-facing contract (iteration 1, evidence: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:37-44`).\n63: - Blind global replacement of `deep-loop-runtime` / `deep-loop-workflows`: unsafe because import depth, generated-contract literals, path expectation tests, and historical prose need separate treatment (iteration 2).\n64: - Fully decoupling runtime compiler/test tooling from system-spec-kit during this merge: unnecessary and risky because production dependency self-containment is already guarded (iteration 3).\n65: <!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n66: \n67: <!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n68: ## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n69: \n70: - Deferring `deep-ai-council/scripts/replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs` to child 003 only: ruled out because it is an internal executable runtime-script lookup (iteration 2, evidence: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs:21-66`).\n71: - Treating the four-row Stage 3b table as complete: ruled out because artifact-root and council anchor fixtures are load-bearing for the stated validation gates (iteration 3).\n72: <!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n73: \n74: <!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n75: ## 11A. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n76: \n77: [None yet]\n78: <!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n79: \n80: <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n81: ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n82: \n83: Reference migration: classify command assets, agent paths, READMEs, graph metadata, advisor corpus/scorer references, model profiles, and intentionally stable public command/agent names.\n84: <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n85: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n86: \n87: ## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n88: \n89: - Bound spec folder: `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research`.\n90: - Bound artifact directory: `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-9`.\n91: - Packet spec says this phase is read-only research over structural layout, coupling repair, reference migration, advisor-corpus handling, and fallback-router wiring [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/spec.md:68-75].\n92: - Packet plan defines the fan-out executor payload and notes `iterations` is the JSON field while `iters` is only a repeatable CLI flag alias [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/plan.md:71-85].\n93: - `resource-map.md` was not present in the spec folder at init; skipping coverage gate.\n94: - Memory trigger lookup failed with `MCP error -32000: Connection closed`; this lineage uses direct file evidence plus stale-code-graph status as context.\n95: - Code graph status is stale because git HEAD changed and the scope excludes commands/agents/specs, so structural claims must be verified by Grep/Read rather than graph-only evidence.\n96: \n97: ## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n98: \n99: - Max iterations: 10\n100: - Min iterations before convergence: 3\n101: - Convergence threshold: 0.05\n102: - Stop policy: convergence\n103: - Per-iteration budget: 12 tool calls maximum\n104: - Progressive synthesis: true\n105: - Session ID: `fanout-gpt55-fast-9-1783486518892-2qss01`\n106: - Executor: `cli-opencode model=openai/gpt-5.5-fast`\n107: - Current generation: 1\n108: - Started: 2026-07-08T05:12:01Z\n\n(End of file - total 108 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deep Research Strategy - gpt55-fast-9\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nThis detached fan-out lineage validates the proposed deep-loop unification design using the bound artifact directory as the state boundary.\n\n## 2. TOPIC\n\nValidate and stress-test the merge design for folding deep-loop-runtime into deep-loop-workflows as system-deep-loop: structural layout, bidirectional path-coupling repair, the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow, reference migration across commands/agents/READMEs/advisor-corpus, and whether fallback-router.ts should be wired for real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback.\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n\n- [x] Is the proposed `system-deep-loop/` layout with nested `runtime/` structurally coherent without creating duplicate skill identity or mode ambiguity?\n- [x] Are the bidirectional path-coupling repair rules complete for workflow-to-runtime and runtime-to-workflow references after the move?\n- [x] Is the `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow repair complete, including hidden runtime seams and tests beyond the obvious package and tsconfig files?\n- [ ] What command, agent, README, graph metadata, advisor-corpus, and model-prompt references must migrate, and which should intentionally remain stable?\n- [ ] Should `fallback-router.ts` be wired now for GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback, or remain deferred/manual for this research phase?\n<!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-9/deep-research-strategy.md","text":"# Deep Research Strategy - gpt55-fast-9\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nThis detached fan-out lineage validates the proposed deep-loop unification design using the bound artifact directory as the state boundary.\n\n## 2. TOPIC\n\nValidate and stress-test the merge design for folding deep-loop-runtime into deep-loop-workflows as system-deep-loop: structural layout, bidirectional path-coupling repair, the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow, reference migration across commands/agents/READMEs/advisor-corpus, and whether fallback-router.ts should be wired for real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback.\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n\n- [x] Is the proposed `system-deep-loop/` layout with nested `runtime/` structurally coherent without creating duplicate skill identity or mode ambiguity?\n- [x] Are the bidirectional path-coupling repair rules complete for workflow-to-runtime and runtime-to-workflow references after the move?\n- [x] Is the `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow repair complete, including hidden runtime seams and tests beyond the obvious package and tsconfig files?\n- [ ] What command, agent, README, graph metadata, advisor-corpus, and model-prompt references must migrate, and which should intentionally remain stable?\n- [ ] Should `fallback-router.ts` be wired now for GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback, or remain deferred/manual for this research phase?\n<!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n\n## 4. NON-GOALS\n\n- Do not modify `deep-loop-workflows`, `deep-loop-runtime`, command assets, agents, advisor corpora, specs, or READMEs outside this lineage.\n- Do not execute the merge or implement fallback routing.\n- Do not write outside `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-9`.\n\n## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n\n- Stop after legal convergence once all five key questions have evidence-backed answers and at least 3 iterations have completed.\n- Stop at `maxIterations: 10` if convergence does not arrive earlier.\n- Continue past a low-novelty STOP candidate if quality guards lack source diversity or question coverage.\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n\n- [x] Structural layout: coherent if `system-deep-loop` is the single public hub and `runtime/` is backend infrastructure with no routable skill identity or mode metadata (iteration 1; evidence: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:12`, `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:14-17`, `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:64-67`).\n- [x] Path-coupling: Class A and Class B repair directions are correct, but child 002's file table is incomplete; add research/review runtime-capability shims, council orchestrate-session, council replay graph, and a classified runtime-test inventory (iteration 2; evidence: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/orchestrate-session.cjs:16-18`, `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs:21-66`, `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/runtime-capabilities.vitest.ts:10-12`).\n- [x] Tooling-borrow: the four planned compiler/test edits are necessary but incomplete; phase 002 should also cover runtime `artifact-root.cjs`, its test, and `test:council` anchor fixture paths if those gates run before child 003 (iteration 3; evidence: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs:16-19`, `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/artifact-root.vitest.ts:10-25`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/council-playbook-anchor-integrity.vitest.ts:7-67`).\n<!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n## 7. WHAT WORKED\n\n- Paired hub/runtime contract reads: verified the public hub plus frozen backend split and the one-graph-metadata invariant (iteration 1).\n- Executable grep plus targeted reads: found omitted reverse-coupling files and separated imports from prose hits (iteration 2).\n- Validation-gate tracing: starting from the named `test:council` and runtime gates exposed hidden path-sensitive seams (iteration 3).\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n## 8. WHAT FAILED\n\n- Code graph status: stale and scope-excluding commands/agents/specs, so it was not used as proof for structural claims (iteration 1).\n- Broad workflow markdown grep: too noisy for actionable path-coupling classification due to playbooks, changelogs, feature catalogs, and benchmark outputs (iteration 2).\n- Whole-system-spec-kit grep: useful for future child 003 inventory, but too broad for phase 002 blocker classification without gate ownership buckets (iteration 3).\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n\n- Flattening workflow packets and runtime libraries into one directory: contradicts per-mode contract ownership and risks mode ambiguity (iteration 1, evidence: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:64-67`).\n- Keeping `runtime/SKILL.md` discoverable after the merge: contradicts runtime's non-user-facing contract (iteration 1, evidence: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:37-44`).\n- Blind global replacement of `deep-loop-runtime` / `deep-loop-workflows`: unsafe because import depth, generated-contract literals, path expectation tests, and historical prose need separate treatment (iteration 2).\n- Fully decoupling runtime compiler/test tooling from system-spec-kit during this merge: unnecessary and risky because production dependency self-containment is already guarded (iteration 3).\n<!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n\n- Deferring `deep-ai-council/scripts/replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs` to child 003 only: ruled out because it is an internal executable runtime-script lookup (iteration 2, evidence: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs:21-66`).\n- Treating the four-row Stage 3b table as complete: ruled out because artifact-root and council anchor fixtures are load-bearing for the stated validation gates (iteration 3).\n<!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n## 11A. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n\n[None yet]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n\nReference migration: classify command assets, agent paths, READMEs, graph metadata, advisor corpus/scorer references, model profiles, and intentionally stable public command/agent names.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n\n- Bound spec folder: `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research`.\n- Bound artifact directory: `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-9`.\n- Packet spec says this phase is read-only research over structural layout, coupling repair, reference migration, advisor-corpus handling, and fallback-router wiring [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/spec.md:68-75].\n- Packet plan defines the fan-out executor payload and notes `iterations` is the JSON field while `iters` is only a repeatable CLI flag alias [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/plan.md:71-85].\n- `resource-map.md` was not present in the spec folder at init; skipping coverage gate.\n- Memory trigger lookup failed with `MCP error -32000: Connection closed`; this lineage uses direct file evidence plus stale-code-graph status as context.\n- Code graph status is stale because git HEAD changed and the scope excludes commands/agents/specs, so structural claims must be verified by Grep/Read rather than graph-only evidence.\n\n## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n\n- Max iterations: 10\n- Min iterations before convergence: 3\n- Convergence threshold: 0.05\n- Stop policy: convergence\n- Per-iteration budget: 12 tool calls maximum\n- Progressive synthesis: true\n- Session ID: `fanout-gpt55-fast-9-1783486518892-2qss01`\n- Executor: `cli-opencode model=openai/gpt-5.5-fast`\n- Current generation: 1\n- Started: 2026-07-08T05:12:01Z","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":108,"totalLines":108,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-9/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1783488683291,"end":1783488683300}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09a7e4a4727c6b9b016a4de0ab3b908191b9a07ee891953203"}},"id":"prt_f40359d1a001cn9RjnoynwqxuE","sessionID":"ses_0bfcc9e59