t the current table is incomplete and should explicitly include runtime-capability shims, council orchestrate-session, council replay graph, and classified runtime tests.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"question\": \"Is the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow repair complete beyond package and tsconfig files?\",\n      \"answeredIn\": 3,\n      \"answer\": \"The four planned edits are necessary, but phase 002 should also cover artifact-root, artifact-root tests, and test:council anchor fixtures; broader system-spec-kit references belong to child 003 unless their suites are run in phase 002.\"","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-9/deep-research-findings-registry.json","text":"{\n  \"openQuestions\": [\n    \"What command, agent, README, graph metadata, advisor-corpus, and model-prompt references must migrate or remain stable?\",\n    \"Should fallback-router.ts be wired now for GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback?\"\n  ],\n  \"resolvedQuestions\": [\n    {\n      \"question\": \"Is the proposed system-deep-loop/runtime layout structurally coherent without duplicate skill identity or mode ambiguity?\",\n      \"answeredIn\": 1,\n      \"answer\": \"Yes, if system-deep-loop remains the single public hub and runtime is demoted to backend infrastructure without routable skill metadata.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"question\": \"Are bidirectional path-coupling repair rules complete after the move?\",\n      \"answeredIn\": 2,\n      \"answer\": \"The repair directions are correct, but the current table is incomplete and should explicitly include runtime-capability shims, council orchestrate-session, council replay graph, and classified runtime tests.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"question\": \"Is the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow repair complete beyond package and tsconfig files?\",\n     