{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783488744188,"sessionID":"ses_0bfcc9e59ffevWtcj5ONdHm47k","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_S6QHSOAI8JqNZCF9VI6w0Tov","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"fallback-router|fallback router|fallback routing","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime","include":"*.{ts,md,json,cjs}"},"output":"Found 70 matches\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:\n  Line 147: > **Feature File:** [DLR-003](01--executor/fallback-router.md)\n\n  Line 154: Adds typed fallback-route metadata, route trace fields, and startup graph validation for executor fallback routing.\n\n  Line 162: > **Feature File:** [DLR-044](01--executor/fallback-router-typed-reroute.md)\n\n  Line 852: | Executor | `tests/unit/executor-config.vitest.ts`, `tests/unit/executor-audit*.vitest.ts`, `tests/unit/fallback-router.vitest.ts`, `tests/unit/cli-matrix.vitest.ts` | Executor parsing, audit, fallback, and CLI dispatch behavior. |\n\n  Line 871: | DLR-003 | [F003 Fallback router](../feature_catalog/01--executor/fallback-router.md) | [01--executor/fallback-router.md](01--executor/fallback-router.md) |\n\n  Line 912: | DLR-044 | [F042 Fallback-router typed reroute](../feature_catalog/01--executor/fallback-router-typed-reroute.md) | [01--executor/fallback-router-typed-reroute.md](01--executor/fallback-router-typed-reroute.md) |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/README.md:\n  Line 31: | `fallback-router.ts` | Executor fallback routing. |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:\n  Line 57: /** Registry of model profiles available to the fallback router. */\n\n  Line 369:         reason: `unknown model ${failedModelId}; no quota pool available for fallback routing`,\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/01--executor/executor-audit.md:\n  Line 62: - [fallback-router.md](fallback-router.md) — Fallback router\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/01--executor/fallback-router-typed-reroute.md:\n  Line 3: description: \"Adds typed fallback-route metadata, route trace fields, and startup graph validation for executor fallback routing.\"\n\n  Line 5:   - \"fallback-router typed reroute\"\n\n  Line 6:   - \"fallback-router-typed-reroute\"\n\n  Line 7:   - \"fallback-router typed reroute deep-loop-runtime\"\n\n  Line 8:   - \"executor fallback-router typed reroute\"\n\n  Line 20: Adds typed fallback-route metadata, route trace fields, and startup graph validation for executor fallback routing.\n\n  Line 40: | `lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts` | Runtime | typed fallback-router reroute + graph preflight. |\n\n  Line 46: | `tests/unit/fallback-router.vitest.ts` | Test | Primary regression coverage for Fallback-router typed reroute. |\n\n  Line 55: - Feature file path: `01--executor/fallback-router-typed-reroute.md`\n\n  Line 56: - Source phase: `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/030-deep-loop-improved/002-deep-loop-runtime/015-fallback-router-typed-reroute`\n\n  Line 57: - Primary sources: `lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts`, `tests/unit/fallback-router.vitest.ts`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/01--executor/fallback-router.md:\n  Line 5:   - \"fallback router\"\n\n  Line 6:   - \"fallback-router.ts\"\n\n  Line 41: | `lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts` | Runtime | Model registry lookup, fallback target selection, disabled fallback, and fail-fast reasons. |\n\n  Line 47: | `tests/unit/fallback-router.vitest.ts` | Test | Primary regression coverage for Fallback router. |\n\n  Line 56: - Feature file path: `01--executor/fallback-router.md`\n\n  Line 57: - Primary sources: `lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts`, `tests/unit/fallback-router.vitest.ts`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md:\n  Line 11:   - \"fallback router\"\n\n  Line 38: Several deep loops shared the same runtime code. Each needed executor config parsing. Each needed atomic state-log writes and single-writer locking. Each needed a coverage graph that survives a session crash. Each needed Bayesian convergence scoring. Before this skill existed, all of that lived inside `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/` and got reached through MCP tools. The consumer modes depended on the internals of a separate package, every workflow call paid the MCP marshalling and JSON-parse round-trip, and each loop would otherwise duplicate executor config, atomic-state writes, JSONL repair, single-writer locking, coverage-graph ownership, Bayesian scoring and fallback routing.\n\n  Line 44: `deep-loop-runtime` provides three component families through TypeScript imports under `lib/` and `.cjs` script entry points under `scripts/`, plus shared lifecycle, observability, and test-harness helpers surfaced in the catalog. The deep-loop family owns executor config, prompt-pack rendering, post-dispatch validation, atomic state, JSONL repair, loop locking, permissions gating, Bayesian scoring and fallback routing. It also hosts the shared backend contracts the consumer modes ride: a parameterized capability resolver, the artifact-topology seam (`resolveArtifactRoot`), the terminal lifecycle taxonomy (seven `stopReason` plus four `sessionOutcome` values) and a CLI adapter over the loop lock. The coverage-graph family owns the SQLite schema, query builders and convergence-signal extraction. The council family owns multi-seat dispatch, round-state JSONL, adjudicator-verdict scoring, cost guards, session-state hierarchy and the council graph. The workflow modes import what they need. No mode invokes this skill directly, and none of these contracts register an MCP tool. It is the foundation they ride.\n\n  Line 92: `lib/deep-loop/` holds the loop infrastructure. `executor-config` parses per-iteration executor settings from a shared schema so every consumer calls the same executor shape. `executor-audit` appends a provenance block to each iteration JSONL so you can tell which model and CLI produced each iteration. `prompt-pack` renders the iteration prompt template. `post-dispatch-validate` checks that an iteration produced valid markdown, JSONL and delta outputs before the state log accepts them, stamps seekable log-region offsets, and quarantines failed LLM-judge fallback cards. `atomic-state` writes state logs through a tmpfile-plus-rename pattern, adds compare-before-write, SHA-256 integrity helpers, and a deferred writer, so a crash never leaves a partial line and unchanged snapshots can avoid redundant writes. `jsonl-repair` recovers a corrupt trailing line before append and supports lock-held fan-out salvage merges. `loop-lock` enforces single-writer access around state mutations, with heartbeat metadata and opt-in host-local single-flight acquisition. `permissions-gate` checks permission scope before touching sensitive paths. `bayesian-scorer` exports the small Bayesian helpers `computeScore` and `shouldDemote`; `convergence.cjs` builds the typed loop decisions. `fallback-router` picks a replacement executor when the primary one times out and validates typed reroute graphs before dispatch.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/manual_testing_playbook/01--executor/fallback-router-typed-reroute.md:\n  Line 15: Adds typed fallback-route metadata, route trace fields, and startup graph validation for executor fallback routing.\n\n  Line 39: - Feature catalog entry exists at `feature_catalog/01--executor/fallback-router-typed-reroute.md`.\n\n  Line 43: 1. Inspect `lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts` for the implementation contract.\n\n  Line 44: 2. Inspect `tests/unit/fallback-router.vitest.ts` for the matching regression coverage.\n\n  Line 68: | `lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts` | typed fallback-router reroute + graph preflight. |\n\n  Line 74: | `tests/unit/fallback-router.vitest.ts` | Primary regression coverage for Fallback-router typed reroute. |\n\n  Line 82: - Feature catalog entry: `feature_catalog/01--executor/fallback-router-typed-reroute.md`\n\n  Line 83: - Scenario file path: `manual_testing_playbook/01--executor/fallback-router-typed-reroute.md`\n\n  Line 84: - Source phase: `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/030-deep-loop-improved/002-deep-loop-runtime/015-fallback-router-typed-reroute`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/feature_catalog.md:\n  Line 23: | [01--executor](01--executor/) | 4 features | `lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts`, `lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts`, `lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts` |\n\n  Line 88: See [`01--executor/fallback-router.md`](01--executor/fallback-router.md) for full implementation and validation file listings.\n\n  Line 96: Adds typed fallback-route metadata, route trace fields, and startup graph validation for executor fallback routing.\n\n  Line 104: See [`01--executor/fallback-router-typed-reroute.md`](01--executor/fallback-router-typed-reroute.md) for full implementation and validation file listings.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/manual_testing_playbook/01--executor/fallback-router.md:\n  Line 25: - Objective: Confirm fallback router behaves as documented and remains aligned with its implementation and tests.\n\n  Line 39: - Feature catalog entry exists at `feature_catalog/01--executor/fallback-router.md`.\n\n  Line 43: 1. Inspect `lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts` for the implementation contract.\n\n  Line 44: 2. Inspect `tests/unit/fallback-router.vitest.ts` for the primary regression coverage.\n\n  Line 68: | `lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts` | Model registry lookup, fallback target selection, disabled fallback, and fail-fast reasons. |\n\n  Line 74: | `tests/unit/fallback-router.vitest.ts` | Primary regression coverage for Fallback router. |\n\n  Line 82: - Feature catalog entry: `feature_catalog/01--executor/fallback-router.md`\n\n  Line 83: - Scenario file path: `manual_testing_playbook/01--executor/fallback-router.md`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.1.0.0.md:\n  Line 25: - 3.3 Scoring and routing (2 modules: bayesian-scorer, fallback-router)\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/fallback-router.vitest.ts:\n  Line 12: } from '../../lib/deep-loop/fallback-router';\n\n  Line 36: describe('fallback-router', () => {\n\n  Line 105:       reason: 'unknown model missing-model; no quota pool available for fallback routing',\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.0.0.0.md:\n  Line 19: - **Deep-loop support code** — Ten shared TypeScript modules now live under `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/`: executor config, executor audit, prompt-pack rendering, post-dispatch validation, atomic state, JSONL repair, loop locking, permissions, Bayesian scoring, and fallback routing. Each carries a `MODULE:` header per the OpenCode TypeScript style guide.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:\n  Line 4: description: \"Shared deep-loop runtime: executor + prompt-pack + validation + atomic state + coverage-graph + Bayesian scoring + fallback routing.\"\n\n  Line 25: - Bayesian scorin