ck-router\",\n\n  Line 228:     \"causal_summary\": \"Shared runtime infrastructure for deep-review, deep-research and deep-ai-council moved into a peer skill in the 118 FULL_ISOLATE_NO_MCP arc. Executor configuration, audit provenance, prompt rendering, post-dispatch validation, state safety, Bayesian scoring, fallback routing, coverage-graph storage/query/signals, script entry points, SQLite storage and runtime tests now have one discoverable owner outside the system-spec-kit MCP server. lib/council/ adds 5 cjs modules for multi-seat dispatch, round-state JSONL, adjudicator verdict scoring, cost guards and session-state hierarchy per packet 131/001/008 ADR-001 (Runtime Boundary Decision).\",\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/executor-provenance-mismatch.vitest.ts:\n  Line 12: import { type ModelProfile, type ModelRegistry, resolveFallback } from '../../lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.js';\n\n  Line 237: describe('fallback-router approval guard (008)', () => {\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/README.md:\n  Line 30: | `fallback-router.vitest.ts` | `lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts` |\n","metadata":{"matches":70,"truncated":false},"title":"fallback-router|fallback router|fallback routing","time":{"start":1783488744156,"end":1783488744179}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0b83367c150b25e3016a4de0e7e9508191b8744ca20f1779cf"}},"id":"prt_f40368acd001QZZ5Ty8DYMJiiR","sessionID":"ses_0bfcc9e59ffevWtcj5ONdHm47k","messageID":"msg_f403647fd001dbK7pDNAUF125l"}}
