.json description (line 237 area): \\\"COSTAR framework (empirical, benchmark 008; fallback TIDD-EC, avoid RCAF)\\\"\\nglm-5.2.md line 4 description: \\\"COSTAR framework (empirical, benchmark 008; fallback TIDD-EC, avoid RCAF)\\\"\\nSynthesis says: TIE among 4 frameworks at perfect correctness. COSTAR is ranked #1 only because of token efficiency (13 words vs 38/94/94), NOT because of correctness superiority.\\n\\nIs calling COSTAR \\\"the empirical winner\\\" an overclaim? The synthesis explicitly says \\\"TIE\\\" — the 4 perfect frameworks \\\"cannot be statistically separated.\\\" The profile does explain the tie in §3 and §4, but the frontmatter description and model_profiles.json description call it \\\"empirical\\\" without qualification. The \\\"status: empirical\\\" on the JSON entry at line 295 is also unqualified.\\n\\n**Check 3: \\\"status: empirical\\\" justification**\\nThe status field means \\\"backed by benchmark evidence.\\\" COSTAR IS backed by benchmark 008 — it's in the perfect tier. The status doesn't claim...\n  Line 9: {\"pass\":\"glm-bakeoff-evidence-honesty\",\"findings\":[{\"severity\":\"P1\",\"file\":\".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/references/models/glm-5.2.md\",\"issue\":\"Frontmatter description calls COSTAR 'empirical, benchmark 008' as if it were the unique winner; synthesis says TIE among 4 frameworks at perfect correctness (costar=tidd-ec=cidi=race 1.0, margin 0, 90% CI [0,0]). The body §3/§4 honestly disclose the TIE and call it 'best-of-tied + corroborated', but the summary line overclaims.\",\"evidence\":\"line 4: 'COSTAR framework (empirical, benchmark 008; fallback TIDD-EC, avoid RCAF)' vs synthesis.md line 5: 'Verdict: TIE (inside_noise_floor) on ranking key correctness'\"}]}\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-sk-prompt-models-rename/graph-metadata.json:\n  Line 92:     \"causal_summary\": \"The skill `sk-prompt-small-model` is the per-model prompt-craft hub for the non-frontier models dispatched out via the cli- executors (DeepSeek-v4-pro, Kimi-k2.7-code, MiniMax-M3, MiMo-V2.5-Pro, GLM-5.2)\",\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-sk-prompt-models-rename/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:\n  Line 2: > build · mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-sk-prompt-models-rename/002-core-rename/spec.md:\n  Line 154: | Risk | Untracked new files not moving | Orphaned glm-5.2.md / benchmarks/008 | Confirm `mv` carried untracked files; `ls` the new folder |\n","metadata":{"matches":53,"truncated":false},"title":"fallback-router|glm-5\\.2|GLM-5\\.2|MiMo|mimo-v2\\.5-pro","time":{"start":1783488744204,"end":1783488744230}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0b83367c150b25e3016a4de0e7e9788191823fa2bab59f896e"}},"id":"prt_f40368afa001BNc4z6mM8ZD7Hi","sessionID":"ses_0bfcc9e59ffevWtcj5ONdHm47k","messageID":"msg_f403647fd001dbK7pDNAUF125l"}}
