{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783488770396,"sessionID":"ses_0bfcc9e59ffevWtcj5ONdHm47k","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_N9eAAS4LXtI0RAdObkCiCtyR","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json","offset":220,"limit":100},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n220:         \"1,000,000-token context window (largest in the small-model rotation)\",\n221:         \"strongly agentic — sustains 1000+ sequential tool calls (SWE-bench Pro 57.2)\",\n222:         \"token-efficient — 40-60% fewer tokens/trajectory vs frontier models (Opus 4.6 / GPT-5.4)\",\n223:         \"Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe) subscription billing via provider xiaomi-token-plan-ams\",\n224:         \"separate quota pool (xiaomi-token-plan) independent of minimax / cognition pools\",\n225:         \"manual direct-provider reroute available at xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro when configured\"\n226:       ],\n227:       \"weaknesses\": [\n228:         \"long-context quality degrades past ~512k despite the 1M window\",\n229:         \"Token-Plan subscription request-window semantics unverified\",\n230:         \"prompt-framework benchmark 004 used 2 fixtures / single-sample — COSTAR vs RACE tie is within noise\",\n231:         \"visual/illustration tasks: over-accents — spreads orange/gold across most cards, weak color restraint despite clean shapes and a reserved-accent brief (informal bento bake-off, n=1 fixture, 2026-06-22; see references/models/mimo-v2.5-pro.md)\"\n232:       ],\n233:       \"avg_iter_wall_clock_min\": null,\n234:       \"status\": \"active\",\n235:       \"recommended_frameworks\": {\n236:         \"primary\": \"costar\",\n237:         \"fallback\": \"race\",\n238:         \"avoid\": [\n239:           \"tidd-ec\",\n240:           \"cidi\"\n241:         ],\n242:         \"preplanning_density\": \"lean\",\n243:         \"evidence\": {\n244:           \"benchmark\": \"004\",\n245:           \"primary_score\": 1.0,\n246:           \"fallback_score\": 0.9934,\n247:           \"sample\": \"10/10 real MiMo-V2.5-Pro runs at --variant high\",\n248:           \"confidence\": \"high\"\n249:         },\n250:         \"profile_ref\": \"sk-prompt-models/references/models/mimo-v2.5-pro.md\",\n251:         \"status\": \"empirical\"\n252:       }\n253:     },\n254:     {\n255:       \"id\": \"glm-5.2\",\n256:       \"context_length\": 1000000,\n257:       \"tool_calling\": \"native\",\n258:       \"chat_template\": \"default\",\n259:       \"executors\": [\n260:         {\n261:           \"executor\": \"cli-opencode\",\n262:           \"provider\": \"zai-coding-plan\",\n263:           \"quota_pool\": \"zai-coding-plan\",\n264:           \"status\": \"active\",\n265:           \"notes\": \"Z.AI GLM Coding Plan (subscription) via opencode provider `zai-coding-plan` (auth credential 'Z.AI Coding Plan'). Live slug `zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2`; confirmed present via `opencode models zai-coding-plan` 2026-06-28 → glm-4.5-air/glm-4.7/glm-5-turbo/glm-5.1/glm-5.2/glm-5v-turbo. Flagship long-horizon coding model (supersedes the gateway-only glm-5.1 removed in cli-opencode v1.3.15.0). context_length 1,000,000 / 131,072 output per Z.AI docs — opencode `models` did not expose limits, re-verify. Omit `--agent` at top level. GLM has native `reasoning_effort` (high/max); whether opencode `--variant` forwards to it is unverified — smoke-test before relying on it. Thinking is on by default and the Coding Plan endpoint preserves thinking. Re-verify the live slug before automation — Z.AI ids drift (provider also serves glm-4.7 / glm-5.1 / glm-5-turbo).\"\n266:         }\n267:       ],\n268:       \"primary_quota_pool\": \"zai-coding-plan\",\n269:       \"fallback_target\": null,\n270:       \"free_tier\": false,\n271:       \"capability\": {\n272:         \"model_slug\": \"zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2\",\n273:         \"default_variant\": \"high\",\n274:         \"variant_flag\": \"--variant\",\n275:         \"agent_policy\": \"omit-general\",\n276:         \"format_mode\": \"json\",\n277:         \"quota_pool\": \"zai-coding-plan\",\n278:         \"variant_status\": \"accepted-unverified\",\n279:         \"modalities\": [\n280:           \"text\",\n281:           \"image\"\n282:         ],\n283:         \"vision\": \"native vision-to-code; image input via the direct Z.AI Coding Plan multimodal API (base64 image_url block at https://api.z.ai/api/coding/paas/v4/chat/completions) — opencode `--file` does NOT deliver images to this provider per upstream #20802; confirmed live 2026-06-28; see references/models/glm-5.2.md §7\",\n284:         \"notes\": \"Live slug `zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2` confirmed present 2026-06-28 (`opencode models zai-coding-plan`). agent_policy omit-general: do not pass `--agent` at the top level. format_mode json: dispatch via `opencode run --format json` for the normalized token/cost/latency envelope. default_variant high + variant_status accepted-unverified: GLM's native `reasoning_effort` has high/max, but whether opencode `--variant high/max` forwards to it is not confirmed — smoke-test, do not depend on it. Subscription billing: confirm dispatch cost via smoke test. GLM dispatch quirks (Z.AI docs): thinking on by default + preserved thinking on the Coding Plan endpoint; function-calling `tool_choice` only `auto`; streaming tool calls need `tool_stream=true`. Re-verify slug before dispatch (Z.AI ids drift).\"\n285:       },\n286:       \"strengths\": [\n287:         \"dedicated Z.AI GLM Coding Plan subscription pool (`zai-coding-plan`), independent of kimi / minimax / xiaomi pools\",\n288:         \"flagship long-horizon coding model (Z.AI docs: Terminal-Bench 2.1 81.0, SWE-bench Pro 62.1 — both above GLM-5.1)\",\n289:         \"1,000,000-token context for long-file and multi-repo work (128K max output)\",\n290:         \"subscription billing via the Z.AI Coding Plan\",\n291:         \"native reasoning_effort (high/max) + thinking-by-default for complex multi-constraint coding\"\n292:       ],\n293:       \"weaknesses\": [\n294:         \"single executor path (no fallback if the zai-coding-plan pool is exhausted)\",\n295:         \"context_length / max-output recorded from Z.AI docs (1,000,000 / 131,072) — opencode `models` did not expose limits; re-verify on the install\",\n296:         \"--variant ↔ reasoning_effort mapping unverified (GLM has native high/max; opencode forwarding not confirmed)\",\n297:         \"best prompt framework is a TIE among the perfect tier (costar=tidd-ec=cidi=race at correctness 1.0); costar is best-of-tied (tersest + cross-model corroborated), not a decisive single winner — benchmark 008\",\n298:         \"thinking-on-by-default drives high latency variance — 6-161s observed over benchmark 008's 45 small code-gen cells (avg ~26s, ~27x spread); budget generous timeouts, a tight timeout kills the slow tail\",\n299:         \"~1/45 dispatches was a transient infra failure (exit -1, dispatch_failed) in benchmark 008 — expect occasional transient dispatch failures at scale; retry the cell rather than treating it as a model error\"\n300:       ],\n301:       \"avg_iter_wall_clock_min\": null,\n302:       \"status\": \"active\",\n303:       \"recommended_frameworks\": {\n304:         \"primary\": \"costar\",\n305:         \"fallback\": \"tidd-ec\",\n306:         \"avoid\": [\n307:           \"rcaf\"\n308:         ],\n309:         \"preplanning_density\": \"lean\",\n310:         \"evidence\": {\n311:           \"benchmark\": \"008-glm-5.2-prompt-framework\",\n312:           \"primary_score\": 1.0,\n313:           \"fallback_score\": 1.0,\n314:           \"sample\": \"5-framework bakeoff on invalid-dominant STRICT VALIDATORS (validate-ipv4 + validate-date + validate-semver), 3 samples/cell, real zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2 dispatches graded by the deterministic hidden-test oracle (grader noop, no LLM-judge bias). Run status SEPARABLE: per-framework correctness costar 1.0 = tidd-ec 1.0 = cidi 1.0 = race 1.0 (perfect tier) > rcaf 0.976 (the ONLY sub-perfect framework; also worst format adherence 0.889). Trust verdict TIE on correctness among the perfect tier (top-pair costar vs tidd-ec, margin 0, 90% CI [0,0]). costar is primary as best-of-tied: perfect correctness + tersest output (13 median words vs tidd-ec 38, cidi/race 94) + cross-model corroboration (also the empirical winner for kimi benchmark 007 and mimo benchmark 004). tidd-ec fallback (perfect, 2nd-tersest). rcaf avoided (only correctness misses + worst format). NOTE: CRAFT (the phase-1 doc-guided default) is NOT in the harness framework registry [rcaf,race,cidi,tidd-ec,costar] so it could not be benchmarked; the empirical winner among the 5 supported frameworks replaces it. 1/45 dispatches was a transient infra failure (exit -1, excluded from scoring).\",\n315:           \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n316:         },\n317:         \"profile_ref\": \"sk-prompt-models/references/models/glm-5.2.md\",\n318:         \"status\": \"empirical\"\n319:       }\n\n(Showing lines 220-319 of 352. Use offset=320 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"        \"1,000,000-token context window (largest in the small-model rotation)\",\n        \"strongly agentic — sustains 1000+ sequential tool calls (SWE-bench Pro 57.2)\",\n        \"token-efficient — 40-60% fewer tokens/trajectory vs frontier models (Opus 4.6 / GPT-5.4)\",\n        \"Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe) subscription billing via provider xiaomi-token-plan-ams\",\n        \"separate quota pool (xiaomi-token-plan) independent of minimax / cognition pools\",\n        \"manual direct-provider reroute available at xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro when configured\"\n      ],\n      \"weaknesses\": [\n        \"long-context quality degrades past ~512k despite the 1M window\",\n        \"Token-Plan subscription request-window semantics unverified\",\n        \"prompt-framework benchmark 004 used 2 fixtures / single-sample — COSTAR vs RACE tie is within noise\",\n        \"visual/illustration tasks: over-accents — spreads orange/gold across most cards, weak color restraint despite clean shapes and a reserved-accent brief (informal bento bake-off, n=1 fixture, 2026-06-22; see references/models/mimo-v2.5-pro.md)\"\n      ],\n      \"avg_iter_wall_clock_min\": null,\n      \"status\": \"active\",\n      \"recommended_frameworks\": {\n        \"primary\": \"costar\",\n        \"fallback\": \"race\",\n        \"avoid\": [\n          \"tidd-ec\",","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json","text":"        \"1,000,000-token context window (largest in the small-model rotation)\",\n        \"strongly agentic — sustains 1000+ sequential tool calls (SWE-bench Pro 57.2)\",\n        \"token-efficient — 40-60% fewer tokens/trajectory vs frontier models (Opus 4.6 / GPT-5.4)\",\n        \"Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe) subscription billing via provider xiaomi-token-plan-ams\",\n        \"separate quota pool (xiaomi-token-plan) independent of minimax / cognition pools\",\n        \"manual direct-provider reroute available at xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro when configured\"\n      ],\n      \"weaknesses\": [\n        \"long-context quality degrades past ~512k despite the 1M window\",\n        \"Token-Plan subscription request-window semantics unverified\",\n        \"prompt-framework benchmark 004 used 2 fixtures / single-sample — COSTAR vs RACE tie is within noise\",\n        \"visual/illustration tasks: over-accents — spreads orange/gold across most cards, weak color restraint despite clean shapes and a reserved-accent brief (informal bento bake-off, n=1 fixture, 2026-06-22; see references/models/mimo-v2.5-pro.md)\"\n      ],\n      \"avg_iter_wall_clock_min\": null,\n      \"status\": \"active\",\n      \"recommended_frameworks\": {\n        \"primary\": \"costar\",\n        \"fallback\": \"race\",\n        \"avoid\": [\n          \"tidd-ec\",\n          \"cidi\"\n        ],\n        \"preplanning_density\": \"lean\",\n        \"evidence\": {\n          \"benchmark\": \"004\",\n          \"primary_score\": 1.0,\n          \"fallback_score\": 0.9934,\n          \"sample\": \"10/10 real MiMo-V2.5-Pro runs at --variant high\",\n          \"confidence\": \"high\"\n        },\n        \"profile_ref\": \"sk-prompt-models/references/models/mimo-v2.5-pro.md\",\n        \"status\": \"empirical\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"glm-5.2\",\n      \"context_length\": 1000000,\n      \"tool_calling\": \"native\",\n      \"chat_template\": \"default\",\n      \"executors\": [\n        {\n          \"executor\": \"cli-opencode\",\n          \"provider\": \"zai-coding-plan\",\n          \"quota_pool\": \"zai-coding-plan\",\n          \"status\": \"active\",\n          \"notes\": \"Z.AI GLM Coding Plan (subscription) via opencode provider `zai-coding-plan` (auth credential 'Z.AI Coding Plan'). Live slug `zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2`; confirmed present via `opencode models zai-coding-plan` 2026-06-28 → glm-4.5-air/glm-4.7/glm-5-turbo/glm-5.1/glm-5.2/glm-5v-turbo. Flagship long-horizon coding model (supersedes the gateway-only glm-5.1 removed in cli-opencode v1.3.15.0). context_length 1,000,000 / 131,072 output per Z.AI docs — opencode `models` did not expose limits, re-verify. Omit `--agent` at top level. GLM has native `reasoning_effort` (high/max); whether opencode `--variant` forwards to it is unverified — smoke-test before relying on it. Thinking is on by default and the Coding Plan endpoint preserves thinking. Re-verify the live slug before automation — Z.AI ids drift (provider also serves glm-4.7 / glm-5.1 / glm-5-turbo).\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"primary_quota_pool\": \"zai-coding-plan\",\n      \"fallback_target\": null,\n      \"free_tier\": false,\n      \"capability\": {\n        \"model_slug\": \"zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2\",\n        \"default_variant\": \"high\",\n        \"variant_flag\": \"--variant\",\n        \"agent_policy\": \"omit-general\",\n        \"format_mode\": \"json\",\n        \"quota_pool\": \"zai-coding-plan\",\n        \"variant_status\": \"accepted-unverified\",\n        \"modalities\": [\n          \"text\",\n          \"image\"\n        ],\n        \"vision\": \"native vision-to-code; image input via the direct Z.AI Coding Plan multimodal API (base64 image_url block at https://api.z.ai/api/coding/paas/v4/chat/completions) — opencode `--file` does NOT deliver images to this provider per upstream #20802; confirmed live 2026-06-28; see references/models/glm-5.2.md §7\",\n        \"notes\": \"Live slug `zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2` confirmed present 2026-06-28 (`opencode models zai-coding-plan`). agent_policy omit-general: do not pass `--agent` at the top level. format_mode json: dispatch via `opencode run --format json` for the normalized token/cost/latency envelope. default_variant high + variant_status accepted-unverified: GLM's native `reasoning_effort` has high/max, but whether opencode `--variant high/max` forwards to it is not confirmed — smoke-test, do not depend on it. Subscription billing: confirm dispatch cost via smoke test. GLM dispatch quirks (Z.AI docs): thinking on by default + preserved thinking on the Coding Plan endpoint; function-calling `tool_choice` only `auto`; streaming tool calls need `tool_stream=true`. Re-verify slug before dispatch (Z.AI ids drift).\"\n      },\n      \"strengths\": [\n        \"dedicated Z.AI GLM Coding Plan subscription pool (`zai-coding-plan`), independent of kimi / minimax / xiaomi pools\",\n        \"flagship long-horizon coding model (Z.AI docs: Terminal-Bench 2.1 81.0, SWE-bench Pro 62.1 — both above GLM-5.1)\",\n        \"1,000,000-token context for long-file and multi-repo work (128K max output)\",\n        \"subscription billing via the Z.AI Coding Plan\",\n        \"native reasoning_effort (high/max) + thinking-by-default for complex multi-constraint coding\"\n      ],\n      \"weaknesses\": [\n        \"single executor path (no fallback if the zai-coding-plan pool is exhausted)\",\n        \"context_length / max-output recorded from Z.AI docs (1,000,000 / 131,072) — opencode `models` did not expose limits; re-verify on the install\",\n        \"--variant ↔ reasoning_effort mapping unverified (GLM has native high/max; opencode forwarding not confirmed)\",\n        \"best prompt framework is a TIE among the perfect tier (costar=tidd-ec=cidi=race at correctness 1.0); costar is best-of-tied (tersest + cross-model corroborated), not a decisive single winner — benchmark 008\",\n        \"thinking-on-by-default drives high latency variance — 6-161s observed over benchmark 008's 45 small code-gen cells (avg ~26s, ~27x spread); budget generous timeouts, a tight timeout kills the slow tail\",\n        \"~1/45 dispatches was a transient infra failure (exit -1, dispatch_failed) in benchmark 008 — expect occasional transient dispatch failures at scale; retry the cell rather than treating it as a model error\"\n      ],\n      \"avg_iter_wall_clock_min\": null,\n      \"status\": \"active\",\n      \"recommended_frameworks\": {\n        \"primary\": \"costar\",\n        \"fallback\": \"tidd-ec\",\n        \"avoid\": [\n          \"rcaf\"\n        ],\n        \"preplanning_density\": \"lean\",\n        \"evidence\": {\n          \"benchmark\": \"008-glm-5.2-prompt-framework\",\n          \"primary_score\": 1.0,\n          \"fallback_score\": 1.0,\n          \"sample\": \"5-framework bakeoff on invalid-dominant STRICT VALIDATORS (validate-ipv4 + validate-date + validate-semver), 3 samples/cell, real zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2 dispatches graded by the deterministic hidden-test oracle (grader noop, no LLM-judge bias). Run status SEPARABLE: per-framework correctness costar 1.0 = tidd-ec 1.0 = cidi 1.0 = race 1.0 (perfect tier) > rcaf 0.976 (the ONLY sub-perfect framework; also worst format adherence 0.889). Trust verdict TIE on correctness among the perfect tier (top-pair costar vs tidd-ec, margin 0, 90% CI [0,0]). costar is primary as best-of-tied: perfect correctness + tersest output (13 median words vs tidd-ec 38, cidi/race 94) + cross-model corroboration (also the empirical winner for kimi benchmark 007 and mimo benchmark 004). tidd-ec fallback (perfect, 2nd-tersest). rcaf avoided (only correctness misses + worst format). NOTE: CRAFT (the phase-1 doc-guided default) is NOT in the harness framework registry [rcaf,race,cidi,tidd-ec,costar] so it could not be benchmarked; the empirical winner among the 5 supported frameworks replaces it. 1/45 dispatches was a transient infra failure (exit -1, excluded from scoring).\",\n          \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n        },\n        \"profile_ref\": \"sk-prompt-models/references/models/glm-5.2.md\",\n        \"status\": \"empirical\"\n      }","lineStart":220,"lineEnd":319,"totalLines":352,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json","time":{"start":1783488770392,"end":1783488770395}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f056d3287fecd92016a4de102443c8191974c76f7e650db4e"}},"id":"prt_f4036f13f001PnIjTU5KQ3t8Z4","sessionID":"ses_0bfcc9e59ffevWtcj5ONdHm47k","messageID":"msg_f4036cade001aoroB5mhJ9ys4r"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783488770404,"sessionID":"ses_0bfcc9e59ffevWtcj5ONdHm47k","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_JC40H9EcyCtw8XQ3895zxGFv","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md","offset":228,"limit":75},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n228: | Token Plan not configured | `MINIMAX_TOKEN_OK=0` | **ASK user** to run `opencode auth login` → MiniMax Token Plan — never substitute silently |\n229: | Direct API explicitly requested | `MINIMAX_DIRECT_OK=1` | Proceed with `--model minimax/MiniMax-M3` (pay-per-token; confirm the live id via `opencode models minimax`) |\n230: | Direct API requested, not configured | `MINIMAX_DIRECT_OK=0` | **ASK user** to run `opencode providers login minimax` (needs `MINIMAX_API_KEY`) — never substitute silently |\n231: \n232: **MiMo routing** (Xiaomi Token Plan Europe and Xiaomi Direct API; explicitly-selectable — first match wins):\n233: \n234: | State | Condition | Action |\n235: |-------|-----------|--------|\n236: | MiMo requested (default) | `XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=1` | Proceed with `--model xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro --variant high` (high reasoning is the standing default — opencode maps low/medium/high to MiMo's reasoning effort) — **omit `--agent`** (`--agent general` warns and falls back on opencode 1.15.13); confirm the live id via `opencode models xiaomi` |\n237: | MiMo speed variant requested (\"ultraspeed\", latency-sensitive checks/smokes) | `XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=1` | Proceed with `--model xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed --variant high` — low-latency MiMo-V2.5-Pro serving tier, same COSTAR prompt contract as the standard model |\n238: | Direct API not configured | `XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=0` | **ASK user** to run `opencode providers login xiaomi` — never substitute silently |\n239: | Token Plan explicitly requested | `XIAOMI_OK=1` | Proceed with `--model xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro --variant high` — NOTE: observed not resolving on this install 2026-06-11 (ProviderModelNotFoundError surfaced as 'Unexpected server error'); re-auth via `opencode auth login` or use the `xiaomi` Direct API instead |\n240: | Token Plan requested, not configured | `XIAOMI_OK=0` | **ASK user** to run `opencode auth login` → Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe) — never substitute silently |\n241: \n242: **User prompt template — default missing, fallback configured:**\n243: \n244: ```\n245: The skill default `deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro` is not configured on this machine.\n246: A configured fallback is available. Pick one:\n247:   A) Use `openai/gpt-5.5-pro --variant high` (OpenAI premium, configured now — paid)\n248:   B) Use `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro --variant high` (Xiaomi Direct API, configured now) — or `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed --variant high` for latency-sensitive runs\n249:   C) Use `kimi-for-coding/k2p7` (Kimi For Coding plan, configured now — subscription)\n250:   D) Run `opencode providers login deepseek` first, then retry the original dispatch\n251:   E) Name a different model — paste the `--model <provider/model>` you want to use\n252: ```\n253: \n254: **User prompt template — all providers missing:**\n255: \n256: ```\n257: No supported providers are configured on this machine. Run one:\n258:   - `opencode providers login deepseek`     (recommended — default for cli-opencode)\n259:   - `opencode auth login`                   (MiniMax Token Plan — default MiniMax path; pick \"MiniMax Token Plan (minimax.io)\" → provider minimax-coding-plan; model minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3)\n260:   - `opencode providers login minimax`      (MiniMax Direct API — pay-per-token; needs MINIMAX_API_KEY; model minimax/MiniMax-M3)\n261:   - `opencode auth login`                   (Xiaomi Token Plan — default Xiaomi path; pick \"Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe)\" → provider xiaomi-token-plan-ams; model xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro)\n262:   - `opencode providers login xiaomi`       (Xiaomi Direct API — pay-per-token; models xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro and xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed)\n263:   - `opencode auth login`                   (Kimi For Coding plan — Kimi/Moonshot coding subscription; provider kimi-for-coding; model kimi-for-coding/k2p7)\n264:   - `opencode auth login`                   (Z.AI GLM Coding Plan — GLM coding subscription; provider zai-coding-plan; model zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2)\n265:   - `opencode providers login openai`       (OpenAI premium alternative — paid)\n266: Which would you like to set up? Confirm when login finishes; the skill will retry the original dispatch.\n267: ```\n268: \n269: **Error-recovery contract.** If a dispatch returns an auth error after pre-flight passed (credential expired or rotated), invalidate the cache, rerun the pre-flight, and apply the same decision tree before retrying. Never substitute a model the user didn't approve.\n270: \n271: ### Default Invocation (Skill Default)\n272: \n273: **Default model + variant + format + dir**: `deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro` · `--variant high` · `--format json` · `--dir <repo-root>`. The repo root pin avoids CWD ambiguity. Direct DeepSeek is the default provider — it gives elevated reasoning at low cost for routine cli-opencode dispatches.\n274: \n275: Use `opencode run --model deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro --variant high --format json --dir <repo-root> \"<prompt>\"`.\n276: \n277: > **The `--agent` flag (read this):** Do NOT pass `--agent` on a top-level `opencode run`. Current opencode treats named agents like `general` as **subagents** and rejects them at the top level, so `--agent general` fails the dispatch outright. When no `--agent` is given, the default agent runs — which is what you want for almost every dispatch. **To run as a specific agent profile, describe the role in the prompt body** (for example, open the prompt with \"Act as a code-review agent: …\"), not via `--agent`. Only pass `--agent <name>` if you have confirmed against `opencode run --help` on the installed version that it accepts that agent at the top level.\n278: \n279: Honor explicit user model, port, and handback phrasing verbatim; otherwise use the default invocation above.\n280: \n281: ### Core Invocation Pattern\n282: \n283: Core flags: `--model`, `--agent`, `--variant`, `--format json`, `--dir`, continuation/session/fork flags, `--share` and `--port` for detached sessions, `--file`, `--thinking`, `--pure`, and log flags.\n284: \n285: > **Non-interactive invocation stdin**: always append `</dev/null` to any non-interactive `opencode run` invocation. Without it, opencode can inherit parent-terminal stdin and trigger the reactive-EOF exit path when that stream closes. See `references/integration_patterns.md` §6.\n286: \n287: > **Registered command dispatch (`--command`)**: slash-command text inside a `run` message is NOT expanded — `opencode run \"/memory:search query\"` delivers the slash text to the model as raw prose, and the command template (router contract, presentation assets, MUST-render envelopes) never enters the session. To execute a registered command non-interactively: `opencode run --command <family>/<name> [flags] \"<args>\"` — the message becomes `$ARGUMENTS`. Registry names are slash-namespaced: `memory/search` for `/memory:search` (a wrong `--command` name fails with the full registry list). Verified on opencode 1.17.4. Consequences: (a) any behavior/adherence probe of a slash command MUST use `--command`, and the raw-text form is only valid as a labeled negative control; (b) inside `` !`…` `` template injections `$ARGUMENTS` expands like `\"$@\"` — one word per argument — so renderer scripts must join argv themselves.\n288: \n289: ### Model Selection\n290: \n291: Run `opencode providers list` to confirm credentials and `opencode models <provider>` for live choices. Default to `deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro --variant high` (direct DeepSeek API); the MiniMax Token Plan default `minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3` (omit `--agent`), the pay-per-token `minimax/MiniMax-M3` (Direct API), `xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro --variant high` (Xiaomi Token Plan Europe — MiMo; high reasoning preset; omit `--agent`), `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro --variant high` (Xiaomi Direct API — MiMo; pay-per-token) and `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed --variant high` (low-latency MiMo tier, same prompt contract) remain available. The Kimi For Coding plan model `kimi-for-coding/k2p7` (\"Kimi K2.7 Code\"; 256k / 262,144-token context; subscription billing — dispatch cost 0; omit `--agent`; `--variant high` accepted but effect benchmark-unverified) is the coding-optimized large-context Kimi path. **Operational caveat (observed 2026-06-17):** on broad / large-repo scopes at `--variant high`, k2p7 over-explores (many sequential reads) and can exceed a 600s timeout WITHOUT emitting — opencode flushes only the final assistant message to stdout, so a killed run yields 0 bytes (looks like a hang, but it was working). Mitigate with a hard read-cap in the prompt (\"read ≤N files then emit\") + a 1200s+ timeout, or omit `--variant`. The Z.AI GLM Coding Plan model `zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2` (\"GLM-5.2\"; flagship long-horizon coding; 1,000,000-token context / 131,072 output per Z.AI docs; subscription billing; omit `--agent`; `--variant`↔`reasoning_effort` mapping unverified — GLM has native high/max, smoke-test before relying on it; thinking on by default + preserved on the Coding Plan endpoint) is the Z.AI direct-provider GLM path, superseding the gateway-only `glm-5.1` removed in v1.3.15.0; confirm the live slug via `opencode models zai-coding-plan`. **Operational (benchmark 008, n=45):** thinking-on drives latency variance 6–161s (avg ~26s) — budget generous timeouts; expect ~1/45... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n292: \n293: Shared small-model facts, context defaults, quota pools, and fallback targets live in `../sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json`.\n294: \n295: ### OpenCode Agent Delegation\n296: \n297: The calling AI is the conductor. OpenCode distinguishes **primary agents** (directly invokable via `--agent <slug>`) from **subagents** (dispatched as Task-tool subagents from a primary).\n298: \n299: #### Primary agents — directly invokable via `--agent`\n300: \n301: OpenCode defines `general`, `plan`, and `orchestrate` as primary agents. **Caveat — never pass `--agent general`:** the current opencode treats `general` as a subagent and rejects it at the top level, and the default agent (used when no `--agent` is given) already covers that case. Pin `--agent plan|orchestrate` only when the task needs that profile AND `opencode run --help` on the installed version confirms top-level acceptance; otherwise state the role in the prompt body.\n302: \n\n(Showing lines 228-302 of 459. Use offset=303 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"| Token Plan not configured | `MINIMAX_TOKEN_OK=0` | **ASK user** to run `opencode auth login` → MiniMax Token Plan — never substitute silently |\n| Direct API explicitly requested | `MINIMAX_DIRECT_OK=1` | Proceed with `--model minimax/MiniMax-M3` (pay-per-token; confirm the live id via `opencode models minimax`) |\n| Direct API requested, not configured | `MINIMAX_DIRECT_OK=0` | **ASK user** to run `opencode providers login minimax` (needs `MINIMAX_API_KEY`) — never substitute silently |\n\n**MiMo routing** (Xiaomi Token Plan Europe and Xiaomi Direct API; explicitly-selectable — first match wins):\n\n| State | Condition | Action |\n|-------|-----------|--------|\n| MiMo requested (default) | `XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=1` | Proceed with `--model xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro --variant high` (high reasoning is the standing default — opencode maps low/medium/high to MiMo's reasoning effort) — **omit `--agent`** (`--agent general` warns and falls back on opencode 1.15.13); confirm the live id via `opencode models xiaomi` |\n| MiMo speed variant requested (\"ultraspeed\", latency-sensitive checks/smokes) | `XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=1` | Proceed with `--model xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed --variant high` — low-latency MiMo-V2.5-Pro serving tier, same COSTAR prompt contract as the standard model |\n| Direct API not configured | `XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=0` | **ASK user** to run `opencode providers login xiaomi` — never substitute silently |\n| Token Plan explicitly requested | `XIAOMI_OK=1` | Proceed with `--model xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro --variant high` — NOTE: observed not resolving on this install 2026-06-11 (ProviderModelNotFoundError surfaced as 'Unexpected server error'); re-auth via `opencode auth login` or use the `xiaomi` Direct API instead |\n| Token Plan requested, not configured | `XIAOMI_OK=0` | **ASK user** to run `opencode auth login` → Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe) — never substitute silently |\n\n**User prompt template — default missing, fallback configured:**\n\n```\nThe skill default `deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro` is not configured on this machine.\nA configured fallback is available. Pick one:\n  A) Use `openai/gpt-5.5-pro --variant high` (OpenAI premium, configured now — paid)","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md","text":"| Token Plan not configured | `MINIMAX_TOKEN_OK=0` | **ASK user** to run `opencode auth login` → MiniMax Token Plan — never substitute silently |\n| Direct API explicitly requested | `MINIMAX_DIRECT_OK=1` | Proceed with `--model minimax/MiniMax-M3` (pay-per-token; confirm the live id via `opencode models minimax`) |\n| Direct API requested, not configured | `MINIMAX_DIRECT_OK=0` | **ASK user** to run `opencode providers login minimax` (needs `MINIMAX_API_KEY`) — never substitute silently |\n\n**MiMo routing** (Xiaomi Token Plan Europe and Xiaomi Direct API; explicitly-selectable — first match wins):\n\n| State | Condition | Action |\n|-------|-----------|--------|\n| MiMo requested (default) | `XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=1` | Proceed with `--model xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro --variant high` (high reasoning is the standing default — opencode maps low/medium/high to MiMo's reasoning effort) — **omit `--agent`** (`--agent general` warns and falls back on opencode 1.15.13); confirm the live id via `opencode models xiaomi` |\n| MiMo speed variant requested (\"ultraspeed\", latency-sensitive checks/smokes) | `XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=1` | Proceed with `--model xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed --variant high` — low-latency MiMo-V2.5-Pro serving tier, same COSTAR prompt contract as the standard model |\n| Direct API not configured | `XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=0` | **ASK user** to run `opencode providers login xiaomi` — never substitute silently |\n| Token Plan explicitly requested | `XIAOMI_OK=1` | Proceed with `--model xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro --variant high` — NOTE: observed not resolving on this install 2026-06-11 (ProviderModelNotFoundError surfaced as 'Unexpected server error'); re-auth via `opencode auth login` or use the `xiaomi` Direct API instead |\n| Token Plan requested, not configured | `XIAOMI_OK=0` | **ASK user** to run `opencode auth login` → Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe) — never substitute silently |\n\n**User prompt template — default missing, fallback configured:**\n\n```\nThe skill default `deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro` is not configured on this machine.\nA configured fallback is available. Pick one:\n  A) Use `openai/gpt-5.5-pro --variant high` (OpenAI premium, configured now — paid)\n  B) Use `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro --variant high` (Xiaomi Direct API, configured now) — or `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed --variant high` for latency-sensitive runs\n  C) Use `kimi-for-coding/k2p7` (Kimi For Coding plan, configured now — subscription)\n  D) Run `opencode providers login deepseek` first, then retry the original dispatch\n  E) Name a different model — paste the `--model <provider/model>` you want to use\n```\n\n**User prompt template — all providers missing:**\n\n```\nNo supported providers are configured on this machine. Run one:\n  - `opencode providers login deepseek`     (recommended — default for cli-opencode)\n  - `opencode auth login`                   (MiniMax Token Plan — default MiniMax path; pick \"MiniMax Token Plan (minimax.io)\" → provider minimax-coding-plan; model minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3)\n  - `opencode providers login minimax`      (MiniMax Direct API — pay-per-token; needs MINIMAX_API_KEY; model minimax/MiniMax-M3)\n  - `opencode auth login`                   (Xiaomi Token Plan — default Xiaomi path; pick \"Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe)\" → provider xiaomi-token-plan-ams; model xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro)\n  - `opencode providers login xiaomi`       (Xiaomi Direct API — pay-per-token; models xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro and xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed)\n  - `opencode auth login`                   (Kimi For Coding plan — Kimi/Moonshot coding subscription; provider kimi-for-coding; model kimi-for-coding/k2p7)\n  - `opencode auth login`                   (Z.AI GLM Coding Plan — GLM coding subscription; provider zai-coding-plan; model zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2)\n  - `opencode providers login openai`       (OpenAI premium alternative — paid)\nWhich would you like to set up? Confirm when login finishes; the skill will retry the original dispatch.\n```\n\n**Error-recovery contract.** If a dispatch returns an auth error after pre-flight passed (credential expired or rotated), invalidate the cache, rerun the pre-flight, and apply the same decision tree before retrying. Never substitute a model the user didn't approve.\n\n### Default Invocation (Skill Default)\n\n**Default model + variant + format + dir**: `deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro` · `--variant high` · `--format json` · `--dir <repo-root>`. The repo root pin avoids CWD ambiguity. Direct DeepSeek is the default provider — it gives elevated reasoning at low cost for routine cli-opencode dispatches.\n\nUse `opencode run --model deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro --variant high --format json --dir <repo-root> \"<prompt>\"`.\n\n> **The `--agent` flag (read this):** Do NOT pass `--agent` on a top-level `opencode run`. Current opencode treats named agents like `general` as **subagents** and rejects them at the top level, so `--agent general` fails the dispatch outright. When no `--agent` is given, the default agent runs — which is what you want for almost every dispatch. **To run as a specific agent profile, describe the role in the prompt body** (for example, open the prompt with \"Act as a code-review agent: …\"), not via `--agent`. Only pass `--agent <name>` if you have confirmed against `opencode run --help` on the installed version that it accepts that agent at the top level.\n\nHonor explicit user model, port, and handback phrasing verbatim; otherwise use the default invocation above.\n\n### Core Invocation Pattern\n\nCore flags: `--model`, `--agent`, `--variant`, `--format json`, `--dir`, continuation/session/fork flags, `--share` and `--port` for detached sessions, `--file`, `--thinking`, `--pure`, and log flags.\n\n> **Non-interactive invocation stdin**: always append `</dev/null` to any non-interactive `opencode run` invocation. Without it, opencode can inherit parent-terminal stdin and trigger the reactive-EOF exit path when that stream closes. See `references/integration_patterns.md` §6.\n\n> **Registered command dispatch (`--command`)**: slash-command text inside a `run` message is NOT expanded — `opencode run \"/memory:search query\"` delivers the slash text to the model as raw prose, and the command template (router contract, presentation assets, MUST-render envelopes) never enters the session. To execute a registered command non-interactively: `opencode run --command <family>/<name> [flags] \"<args>\"` — the message becomes `$ARGUMENTS`. Registry names are slash-namespaced: `memory/search` for `/memory:search` (a wrong `--command` name fails with the full registry list). Verified on opencode 1.17.4. Consequences: (a) any behavior/adherence probe of a slash command MUST use `--command`, and the raw-text form is only valid as a labeled negative control; (b) inside `` !`…` `` template injections `$ARGUMENTS` expands like `\"$@\"` — one word per argument — so renderer scripts must join argv themselves.\n\n### Model Selection\n\nRun `opencode providers list` to confirm credentials and `opencode models <provider>` for live choices. Default to `deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro --variant high` (direct DeepSeek API); the MiniMax Token Plan default `minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3` (omit `--agent`), the pay-per-token `minimax/MiniMax-M3` (Direct API), `xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro --variant high` (Xiaomi Token Plan Europe — MiMo; high reasoning preset; omit `--agent`), `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro --variant high` (Xiaomi Direct API — MiMo; pay-per-token) and `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed --variant high` (low-latency MiMo tier, same prompt contract) remain available. The Kimi For Coding plan model `kimi-for-coding/k2p7` (\"Kimi K2.7 Code\"; 256k / 262,144-token context; subscription billing — dispatch cost 0; omit `--agent`; `--variant high` accepted but effect benchmark-unverified) is the coding-optimized large-context Kimi path. **Operational caveat (observed 2026-06-17):** on broad / large-repo scopes at `--variant high`, k2p7 over-explores (many sequential reads) and can exceed a 600s timeout WITHOUT emitting — opencode flushes only the final assistant message to stdout, so a killed run yields 0 bytes (looks like a hang, but it was working). Mitigate with a hard read-cap in the prompt (\"read ≤N files then emit\") + a 1200s+ timeout, or omit `--variant`. The Z.AI GLM Coding Plan model `zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2` (\"GLM-5.2\"; flagship long-horizon coding; 1,000,000-token context / 131,072 output per Z.AI docs; subscription billing; omit `--agent`; `--variant`↔`reasoning_effort` mapping unverified — GLM has native high/max, smoke-test before relying on it; thinking on by default + preserved on the Coding Plan endpoint) is the Z.AI direct-provider GLM path, superseding the gateway-only `glm-5.1` removed in v1.3.15.0; confirm the live slug via `opencode models zai-coding-plan`. **Operational (benchmark 008, n=45):** thinking-on drives latency variance 6–161s (avg ~26s) — budget generous timeouts; expect ~1/45... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n\nShared small-model facts, context defaults, quota pools, and fallback targets live in `../sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json`.\n\n### OpenCode Agent Delegation\n\nThe calling AI is the conductor. OpenCode distinguishes **primary agents** (directly invokable via `--agent <slug>`) from **subagents** (dispatched as Task-tool subagents from a primary).\n\n#### Primary agents — directly invokable via `--agent`\n\nOpenCode defines `general`, `plan`, and `orchestrate` as primary agents. **Caveat — never pass `--agent general`:** the current opencode treats `general` as a subagent and rejects it at the top level, and the default agent (used when no `--agent` is given) already covers that case. Pin `--agent plan|orchestrate` only when the task needs that profile AND `opencode run --help` on the installed version confirms top-level acceptance; otherwise state the role in the prompt body.\n","lineStart":228,"lineEnd":302,"totalLines":459,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md","time":{"start":1783488770400,"end":1783488770403}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f056d3287fecd92016a4de1024444819180d0c374eb78f3f2"}},"id":"prt_f4036f15b001I7bjfcy1iLxQBt","sessionID":"ses_0bfcc9e59ffevWtcj5ONdHm47k","messageID":"msg_f4036cade001aoroB5mhJ9ys4r"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783488770413,"sessionID":"ses_0bfcc9e59ffevWtcj5ONdHm47k","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_4gPhW0t7SpnO5F8tht5wgEIf","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/assets/prompt_quality_card.md","offset":41,"limit":20},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/assets/prompt_quality_card.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n41: OpenCode dispatches the MiniMax, MiMo, DeepSeek-v4-pro, and Kimi-K2.7 small models, which override or default against the cross-model defaults from the canonical card:\n42: \n43: | Model (dispatchable here) | Override | Profile |\n44: |---|---|---|\n45: | MiniMax M3 (Token Plan default) | TIDD-EC + dense | `../../sk-prompt-models/references/models/minimax-m3.md` |\n46: | MiniMax M3 (Direct API) | TIDD-EC + dense | `../../sk-prompt-models/references/models/minimax-m3.md` |\n47: | MiMo V2.5 Pro (Token Plan) | COSTAR + lean, `--variant high` | `../../sk-prompt-models/references/models/mimo-v2.5-pro.md` |\n48: | MiMo V2.5 Pro (Direct API) | COSTAR + lean, `--variant high` | `../../sk-prompt-models/references/models/mimo-v2.5-pro.md` |\n49: | MiMo V2.5 Pro UltraSpeed (Direct API, low-latency) | COSTAR + lean, `--variant high` | `../../sk-prompt-models/references/models/mimo-v2.5-pro.md` |\n50: | GLM-5.2 (Z.AI GLM Coding Plan) | COSTAR + lean (empirical, benchmark 008) | [`glm-5.2.md`](../../sk-prompt-models/references/models/glm-5.2.md) |\n51: | deepseek-v4-pro / kimi-k2.7-code | default RCAF (no model-specific benchmark; shared default-unverified note) | [`deepseek-v4-pro.md`](../../sk-prompt-models/references/models/deepseek-v4-pro.md) · [`kimi-k2.7-code.md`](../../sk-prompt-models/references/models/kimi-k2.7-code.md) |\n52: \n53: **Executor notes:** Omit `--agent` for all small-model dispatches listed above. OpenCode maps `--variant low/medium/high` to MiMo's reasoning effort; `high` is the standing default for MiMo. MiniMax Token Plan (`minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3`) and Direct API (`minimax/MiniMax-M3`) both serve M3. Xiaomi Token Plan (`xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro`) and Direct API (`xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro`) both serve MiMo-V2.5-Pro; the Direct API additionally serves `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed`, a low-latency tier with the same prompt contract. Ambiguous use-case (1 vs 2 vs 3) prevents the router from picking a path — resolve before dispatch. Always include a self-invocation guard signal when the dispatched session could loop back.\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: ## 4. DELEGATION / PRECEDENCE\n58: \n59: The 3-tier precedence rule (fast path -> model override -> deep path) is canonical in `../../sk-prompt-models/assets/cli_prompt_quality_card.md` and restated in `../SKILL.md`.\n60: \n\n(Showing lines 41-60 of 67. Use offset=61 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"OpenCode dispatches the MiniMax, MiMo, DeepSeek-v4-pro, and Kimi-K2.7 small models, which override or default against the cross-model defaults from the canonical card:\n\n| Model (dispatchable here) | Override | Profile |\n|---|---|---|\n| MiniMax M3 (Token Plan default) | TIDD-EC + dense | `../../sk-prompt-models/references/models/minimax-m3.md` |\n| MiniMax M3 (Direct API) | TIDD-EC + dense | `../../sk-prompt-models/references/models/minimax-m3.md` |\n| MiMo V2.5 Pro (Token Plan) | COSTAR + lean, `--variant high` | `../../sk-prompt-models/references/models/mimo-v2.5-pro.md` |\n| MiMo V2.5 Pro (Direct API) | COSTAR + lean, `--variant high` | `../../sk-prompt-models/references/models/mimo-v2.5-pro.md` |\n| MiMo V2.5 Pro UltraSpeed (Direct API, low-latency) | COSTAR + lean, `--variant high` | `../../sk-prompt-models/references/models/mimo-v2.5-pro.md` |\n| GLM-5.2 (Z.AI GLM Coding Plan) | COSTAR + lean (empirical, benchmark 008) | [`glm-5.2.md`](../../sk-prompt-models/references/models/glm-5.2.md) |\n| deepseek-v4-pro / kimi-k2.7-code | default RCAF (no model-specific benchmark; shared default-unverified note) | [`deepseek-v4-pro.md`](../../sk-prompt-models/references/models/deepseek-v4-pro.md) · [`kimi-k2.7-code.md`](../../sk-prompt-models/references/models/kimi-k2.7-code.md) |\n\n**Executor notes:** Omit `--agent` for all small-model dispatches listed above. OpenCode maps `--variant low/medium/high` to MiMo's reasoning effort; `high` is the standing default for MiMo. MiniMax Token Plan (`minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3`) and Direct API (`minimax/MiniMax-M3`) both serve M3. Xiaomi Token Plan (`xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro`) and Direct API (`xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro`) both serve MiMo-V2.5-Pro; the Direct API additionally serves `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed`, a low-latency tier with the same prompt contract. Ambiguous use-case (1 vs 2 vs 3) prevents the router from picking a path — resolve before dispatch. Always include a self-invocation guard signal when the dispatched session could loop back.\n\n---\n\n## 4. DELEGATION / PRECEDENCE\n\nThe 3-tier precedence rule (fast path -> model override -> deep path) is canonical in `../../sk-prompt-models/assets/cli_prompt_quality_card.md` and restated in `../SKILL.md`.\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/assets/prompt_quality_card.md","text":"OpenCode dispatches the MiniMax, MiMo, DeepSeek-v4-pro, and Kimi-K2.7 small models, which override or default against the cross-model defaults from the canonical card:\n\n| Model (dispatchable here) | Override | Profile |\n|---|---|---|\n| MiniMax M3 (Token Plan default) | TIDD-EC + dense | `../../sk-prompt-models/references/models/minimax-m3.md` |\n| MiniMax M3 (Direct API) | TIDD-EC + dense | `../../sk-prompt-models/references/models/minimax-m3.md` |\n| MiMo V2.5 Pro (Token Plan) | COSTAR + lean, `--variant high` | `../../sk-prompt-models/references/models/mimo-v2.5-pro.md` |\n| MiMo V2.5 Pro (Direct API) | COSTAR + lean, `--variant high` | `../../sk-prompt-models/references/models/mimo-v2.5-pro.md` |\n| MiMo V2.5 Pro UltraSpeed (Direct API, low-latency) | COSTAR + lean, `--variant high` | `../../sk-prompt-models/references/models/mimo-v2.5-pro.md` |\n| GLM-5.2 (Z.AI GLM Coding Plan) | COSTAR + lean (empirical, benchmark 008) | [`glm-5.2.md`](../../sk-prompt-models/references/models/glm-5.2.md) |\n| deepseek-v4-pro / kimi-k2.7-code | default RCAF (no model-specific benchmark; shared default-unverified note) | [`deepseek-v4-pro.md`](../../sk-prompt-models/references/models/deepseek-v4-pro.md) · [`kimi-k2.7-code.md`](../../sk-prompt-models/references/models/kimi-k2.7-code.md) |\n\n**Executor notes:** Omit `--agent` for all small-model dispatches listed above. OpenCode maps `--variant low/medium/high` to MiMo's reasoning effort; `high` is the standing default for MiMo. MiniMax Token Plan (`minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3`) and Direct API (`minimax/MiniMax-M3`) both serve M3. Xiaomi Token Plan (`xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro`) and Direct API (`xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro`) both serve MiMo-V2.5-Pro; the Direct API additionally serves `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed`, a low-latency tier with the same prompt contract. Ambiguous use-case (1 vs 2 vs 3) prevents the router from picking a path — resolve before dispatch. Always include a self-invocation guard signal when the dispatched session could loop back.\n\n---\n\n## 4. DELEGATION / PRECEDENCE\n\nThe 3-tier precedence rule (fast path -> model override -> deep path) is canonical in `../../sk-prompt-models/assets/cli_prompt_quality_card.md` and restated in `../SKILL.md`.\n","lineStart":41,"lineEnd":60,"totalLines":67,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/cli-opencode/assets/prompt_quality_card.md","time":{"start":1783488770406,"end":1783488770408}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f056d3287fecd92016a4de10244508191b7b694d333c102a3"}},"id":"prt_f4036f161001tQoukgVq8HoRn