{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783488809999,"sessionID":"ses_0bfcc9e59ffevWtcj5ONdHm47k","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_uCn6PuR8xJcIZYqHdxTOFakh","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"resolveFallback|createFallbackRouter|validateFallbackGraph","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills","include":"*.{ts,cjs,js}"},"output":"Found 21 matches\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:\n  Line 299: export function validateFallbackGraph(\n\n  Line 320: export function createFallbackRouter(\n\n  Line 324:   validateFallbackGraph(registry, options);\n\n  Line 332:       return resolveFallback(failedModelId, registry, approvedModelIds, context);\n\n  Line 357: export function resolveFallback(\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/fallback-router.vitest.ts:\n  Line 8:   createFallbackRouter,\n\n  Line 11:   resolveFallback,\n\n  Line 38:     expect(resolveFallback('swe-1.6', registryWithFallback('swe-1.6', null))).toEqual({\n\n  Line 45:     expect(resolveFallback('deepseek-v4-pro', registryWithFallback('deepseek-v4-pro', null))).toEqual({\n\n  Line 54:         const result = resolveFallback(source.id, registryWithFallback(source.id, target.id));\n\n  Line 73:     expect(resolveFallback('swe-1.6', registryWithFallback('swe-1.6', 'haiku'))).toEqual({\n\n  Line 81:     expect(resolveFallback('kimi-k2.6', registryWithFallback('kimi-k2.6', 'qwen3.6'))).toEqual({\n\n  Line 88:     expect(resolveFallback('haiku', registryWithFallback('haiku', 'swe-1.6'))).toEqual({\n\n  Line 96:     expect(resolveFallback('swe-1.6', registryWithFallback('swe-1.6', 'missing-model'))).toEqual({\n\n  Line 103:     expect(resolveFallback('missing-model', registryWithFallback('swe-1.6', null))).toEqual({\n\n  Line 128:     const router = createFallbackRouter(registry);\n\n  Line 163:     expect(() => createFallbackRouter(registry)).toThrow(\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/executor-provenance-mismatch.vitest.ts:\n  Line 12: import { type ModelProfile, type ModelRegistry, resolveFallback } from '../../lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.js';\n\n  Line 245:     expect(resolveFallback('swe-1.6', registry, ['swe-1.6', 'haiku'])).toEqual({\n\n  Line 253:     const route = resolveFallback('swe-1.6', registry, ['swe-1.6']);\n\n  Line 259:     expect(resolveFallback('swe-1.6', registry)).toEqual({\n","metadata":{"matches":21,"truncated":false},"title":"resolveFallback|createFallbackRouter|validateFallbackGraph","time":{"start":1783488809950,"end":1783488809997}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_08ba23be03555888016a4de12972188191b502993431517e28"}},"id":"prt_f40378b1d001rkaeltdnIGIM6u","sessionID":"ses_0bfcc9e59ffevWtcj5ONdHm47k","messageID":"msg_f40375b37001fWgcjuYE2uCOoR"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783488809999,"sessionID":"ses_0bfcc9e59ffevWtcj5ONdHm47k","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_d4ZVgWiOjPVrWD6pItapLz8h","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md","offset":55,"limit":60},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n55: ## 2. PROBLEM & PURPOSE\n56: \n57: ### Problem Statement\n58: `deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts` is a fully shipped, unit-tested pure-function library (`resolveFallback`/`createFallbackRouter`/`validateFallbackGraph`, confirmed via direct code read) implementing exactly the \"model A fails, route to model B in a different quota pool\" pattern the operator asked for on `001-reference-research`'s GLM-5.2 → MiMo-v2.5-Pro lineage. It has **zero callers** outside its own test file — `fanout-pool.cjs` only implements same-model retry-with-backoff (`maxRetries`), never a model swap.\n59: \n60: ### Purpose\n61: Wire `resolveFallback()` into `fanout-pool.cjs`'s retry-exhausted branch: on `retryCount >= maxRetries` (or a specific `failureKind`), look up a `ModelRegistry` and re-dispatch a *new* lineage with the fallback model instead of continuing to retry the failed one.\n62: <!-- /ANCHOR:problem -->\n63: \n64: ---\n65: \n66: <!-- ANCHOR:scope -->\n67: ## 3. SCOPE\n68: \n69: ### In Scope\n70: - A `ModelRegistry` config (or inline registry) with at least `glm-5.2 -> mimo-v2.5-pro` (confirmed-valid edge: different `quota_pool`s, no cycle, within default max-1-hop).\n71: - `fanout-pool.cjs` retry-exhausted branch calling `resolveFallback()` and re-dispatching.\n72: \n73: ### Out of Scope\n74: - Any change to `fallback-router.ts` itself — it's already correct and tested.\n75: - A general-purpose fallback UI/config surface beyond what this one use case needs.\n76: \n77: ### Files to Change\n78: \n79: | File Path | Change Type | Description |\n80: |-----------|-------------|-------------|\n81: | `runtime/lib/deep-loop/` or a new small config file | Create | `ModelRegistry` with the glm-5.2/mimo-v2.5-pro edge |\n82: | `runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs` | Edit | Call `resolveFallback()` on retry exhaustion, re-dispatch fallback lineage |\n83: <!-- /ANCHOR:scope -->\n84: \n85: ---\n86: \n87: <!-- ANCHOR:requirements -->\n88: ## 4. REQUIREMENTS\n89: \n90: ### P2 - Optional (can defer with documented reason)\n91: \n92: | ID | Requirement | Acceptance Criteria |\n93: |----|-------------|---------------------|\n94: | REQ-001 | GLM-5.2 lineage auto-substitutes MiMo-v2.5-Pro on retry exhaustion | A forced-failure test on a `glm52` replica produces a `mimo-v2.5-pro` replacement replica, not a fourth same-model retry |\n95: | REQ-002 | `fallback-router.ts` itself remains unmodified | The module's own existing unit tests still pass unchanged |\n96: | REQ-003 | Fallback substitution is logged/attributable | A re-dispatched fallback replica's label makes clear it substituted for a failed `glm52-N` replica, not silently indistinguishable |\n97: <!-- /ANCHOR:requirements -->\n98: \n99: ---\n100: \n101: <!-- ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n102: ## 5. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n103: \n104: - **SC-001**: `fallback-router.ts` has a real, non-test caller.\n105: - **SC-002**: 001-reference-research's own GLM-5.2 lineage (if this lands before that phase re-runs) no longer needs the manual operator-mediated re-dispatch workaround documented in `001-reference-research/plan.md`.\n106: <!-- /ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n107: \n108: ---\n109: \n110: <!-- ANCHOR:risks -->\n111: ## 6. RISKS & DEPENDENCIES\n112: \n113: | Type | Item | Impact | Mitigation |\n114: |------|------|--------|------------|\n\n(Showing lines 55-114 of 124. Use offset=115 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"## 2. PROBLEM & PURPOSE\n\n### Problem Statement\n`deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts` is a fully shipped, unit-tested pure-function library (`resolveFallback`/`createFallbackRouter`/`validateFallbackGraph`, confirmed via direct code read) implementing exactly the \"model A fails, route to model B in a different quota pool\" pattern the operator asked for on `001-reference-research`'s GLM-5.2 → MiMo-v2.5-Pro lineage. It has **zero callers** outside its own test file — `fanout-pool.cjs` only implements same-model retry-with-backoff (`maxRetries`), never a model swap.\n\n### Purpose\nWire `resolveFallback()` into `fanout-pool.cjs`'s retry-exhausted branch: on `retryCount >= maxRetries` (or a specific `failureKind`), look up a `ModelRegistry` and re-dispatch a *new* lineage with the fallback model instead of continuing to retry the failed one.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:problem -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:scope -->\n## 3. SCOPE\n\n### In Scope\n- A `ModelRegistry` config (or inline registry) with at least `glm-5.2 -> mimo-v2.5-pro` (confirmed-valid edge: different `quota_pool`s, no cycle, within default max-1-hop).\n- `fanout-pool.cjs` retry-exhausted branch calling `resolveFallback()` and re-dispatching.\n\n### Out of Scope\n- Any change to `fallback-router.ts` itself — it's already correct and tested.","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md","text":"## 2. PROBLEM & PURPOSE\n\n### Problem Statement\n`deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts` is a fully shipped, unit-tested pure-function library (`resolveFallback`/`createFallbackRouter`/`validateFallbackGraph`, confirmed via direct code read) implementing exactly the \"model A fails, route to model B in a different quota pool\" pattern the operator asked for on `001-reference-research`'s GLM-5.2 → MiMo-v2.5-Pro lineage. It has **zero callers** outside its own test file — `fanout-pool.cjs` only implements same-model retry-with-backoff (`maxRetries`), never a model swap.\n\n### Purpose\nWire `resolveFallback()` into `fanout-pool.cjs`'s retry-exhausted branch: on `retryCount >= maxRetries` (or a specific `failureKind`), look up a `ModelRegistry` and re-dispatch a *new* lineage with the fallback model instead of continuing to retry the failed one.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:problem -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:scope -->\n## 3. SCOPE\n\n### In Scope\n- A `ModelRegistry` config (or inline registry) with at least `glm-5.2 -> mimo-v2.5-pro` (confirmed-valid edge: different `quota_pool`s, no cycle, within default max-1-hop).\n- `fanout-pool.cjs` retry-exhausted branch calling `resolveFallback()` and re-dispatching.\n\n### Out of Scope\n- Any change to `fallback-router.ts` itself — it's already correct and tested.\n- A general-purpose fallback UI/config surface beyond what this one use case needs.\n\n### Files to Change\n\n| File Path | Change Type | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|-------------|\n| `runtime/lib/deep-loop/` or a new small config file | Create | `ModelRegistry` with the glm-5.2/mimo-v2.5-pro edge |\n| `runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs` | Edit | Call `resolveFallback()` on retry exhaustion, re-dispatch fallback lineage |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:scope -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:requirements -->\n## 4. REQUIREMENTS\n\n### P2 - Optional (can defer with documented reason)\n\n| ID | Requirement | Acceptance Criteria |\n|----|-------------|---------------------|\n| REQ-001 | GLM-5.2 lineage auto-substitutes MiMo-v2.5-Pro on retry exhaustion | A forced-failure test on a `glm52` replica produces a `mimo-v2.5-pro` replacement replica, not a fourth same-model retry |\n| REQ-002 | `fallback-router.ts` itself remains unmodified | The module's own existing unit tests still pass unchanged |\n| REQ-003 | Fallback substitution is logged/attributable | A re-dispatched fallback replica's label makes clear it substituted for a failed `glm52-N` replica, not silently indistinguishable |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:requirements -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n## 5. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n\n- **SC-001**: `fallback-router.ts` has a real, non-test caller.\n- **SC-002**: 001-reference-research's own GLM-5.2 lineage (if this lands before that phase re-runs) no longer needs the manual operator-mediated re-dispatch workaround documented in `001-reference-research/plan.md`.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:risks -->\n## 6. RISKS & DEPENDENCIES\n\n| Type | Item | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|------|--------|------------|","lineStart":55,"lineEnd":114,"totalLines":124,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md","time":{"start":1783488809985,"end":1783488809998}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_08ba23be03555888016a4de12972208191a9096a72f18a9cd9"}},"id":"prt_f40378bdf001pvgzJ3VYz5nxfa","sessionID":"ses_0bfcc9e59ffevWtcj5ONdHm47k","messageID":"msg_f40375b37001fWgcjuYE2uCOoR"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783488810000,"sessionID":"ses_0bfcc9e59ffevWtcj5ONdHm47k","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_EK2m6xVYJ6Rfx0ESQHBd5thV","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/plan.md","offset":55,"limit":75},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/plan.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n55: - [ ] `ModelRegistry` with the `glm-5.2 -> mimo-v2.5-pro` edge exists and validates.\n56: - [ ] `fanout-pool.cjs` calls `resolveFallback()` on retry exhaustion.\n57: - [ ] A forced-failure integration test confirms the fallback lineage actually dispatches.\n58: <!-- /ANCHOR:quality-gates -->\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: <!-- ANCHOR:architecture -->\n63: ## 3. ARCHITECTURE\n64: \n65: ### Pattern\n66: Minimal addition at the existing retry-exhaustion decision point in `fanout-pool.cjs`, reusing `fallback-router.ts` as-is (no changes to that module).\n67: \n68: ### Registry entry\n69: \n70: ```json\n71: {\n72:   \"models\": [\n73:     { \"id\": \"glm-5.2\", \"quota_pool\": \"zai-coding-plan\", \"fallback_target\": \"mimo-v2.5-pro\" },\n74:     { \"id\": \"mimo-v2.5-pro\", \"quota_pool\": \"xiaomi-token-plan\", \"fallback_target\": null }\n75:   ]\n76: }\n77: ```\n78: <!-- /ANCHOR:architecture -->\n79: \n80: ---\n81: \n82: <!-- ANCHOR:phases -->\n83: ## 4. IMPLEMENTATION PHASES\n84: \n85: ### Phase 1: Setup\n86: - [ ] Operator scope decision.\n87: - [ ] Author the `ModelRegistry` entry above.\n88: \n89: ### Phase 2: Core Implementation\n90: - [ ] Add `resolveFallback()` call in `fanout-pool.cjs`'s retry-exhausted branch; on `action: 'fallback'`, re-dispatch a new lineage with `target` as its model, same label family.\n91: \n92: ### Phase 3: Verification\n93: - [ ] Forced-failure integration test: a `glm52` replica configured to fail every attempt produces a `mimo-v2.5-pro` replacement, not a 4th same-model retry.\n94: - [ ] Existing `fallback-router.vitest.ts` unaffected (module itself unchanged).\n95: <!-- /ANCHOR:phases -->\n96: \n97: ---\n98: \n99: <!-- ANCHOR:testing -->\n100: ## 5. TESTING STRATEGY\n101: \n102: | Test Type | Scope | Tools |\n103: |-----------|-------|-------|\n104: | Integration | Forced-failure fallback dispatch | New vitest case in `runtime/tests/unit/` |\n105: <!-- /ANCHOR:testing -->\n106: \n107: ---\n108: \n109: <!-- ANCHOR:dependencies -->\n110: ## 6. DEPENDENCIES\n111: \n112: | Dependency | Type | Status | Impact if Blocked |\n113: |------------|------|--------|-------------------|\n114: | `fallback-router.ts` | Internal | Already shipped, unchanged | N/A |\n115: <!-- /ANCHOR:dependencies -->\n116: \n117: ---\n118: \n119: <!-- ANCHOR:rollback -->\n120: ## 7. ROLLBACK PLAN\n121: \n122: - **Trigger**: The new call site introduces a regression in the existing retry path.\n123: - **Procedure**: Revert the single `fanout-pool.cjs` edit; `fallback-router.ts` and the registry file are additive and harmless to leave in place.\n124: <!-- /ANCHOR:rollback -->\n\n(End of file - total 124 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"- [ ] `ModelRegistry` with the `glm-5.2 -> mimo-v2.5-pro` edge exists and validates.\n- [ ] `fanout-pool.cjs` calls `resolveFallback()` on retry exhaustion.\n- [ ] A forced-failure integration test confirms the fallback lineage actually dispatches.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:quality-gates -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:architecture -->\n## 3. ARCHITECTURE\n\n### Pattern\nMinimal addition at the existing retry-exhaustion decision point in `fanout-pool.cjs`, reusing `fallback-router.ts` as-is (no changes to that module).\n\n### Registry entry\n\n```json\n{\n  \"models\": [\n    { \"id\": \"glm-5.2\", \"quota_pool\": \"zai-coding-plan\", \"fallback_target\": \"mimo-v2.5-pro\" },\n    { \"id\": \"mimo-v2.5-pro\", \"quota_pool\": \"xiaomi-token-plan\", \"fallback_target\": null }","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/plan.md","text":"- [ ] `ModelRegistry` with the `glm-5.2 -> mimo-v2.5-pro` edge exists and validates.\n- [ ] `fanout-pool.cjs` calls `resolveFallback()` on retry exhaustion.\n- [ ] A forced-failure integration test confirms the fallback lineage actually dispatches.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:quality-gates -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:architecture -->\n## 3. ARCHITECTURE\n\n### Pattern\nMinimal addition at the existing retry-exhaustion decision point in `fanout-pool.cjs`, reusing `fallback-router.ts` as-is (no changes to that module).\n\n### Registry entry\n\n```json\n{\n  \"models\": [\n    { \"id\": \"glm-5.2\", \"quota_pool\": \"zai-coding-plan\", \"fallback_target\": \"mimo-v2.5-pro\" },\n    { \"id\": \"mimo-v2.5-pro\", \"quota_pool\": \"xiaomi-token-plan\", \"fallback_target\": null }\n  ]\n}\n```\n<!-- /ANCHOR:architecture -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:phases -->\n## 4. IMPLEMENTATION PHASES\n\n### Phase 1: Setup\n- [ ] Operator scope decision.\n- [ ] Author the `ModelRegistry` entry above.\n\n### Phase 2: Core Implementation\n- [ ] Add `resolveFallback()` call in `fanout-pool.cjs`'s retry-exhausted branch; on `action: 'fallback'`, re-dispatch a new lineage with `target` as its model, same label family.\n\n### Phase 3: Verification\n- [ ] Forced-failure integration test: a `glm52` replica configured to fail every attempt produces a `mimo-v2.5-pro` replacement, not a 4th same-model retry.\n- [ ] Existing `fallback-router.vitest.ts` unaffected (module itself unchanged).\n<!-- /ANCHOR:phases -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:testing -->\n## 5. TESTING STRATEGY\n\n| Test Type | Scope | Tools |\n|-----------|-------|-------|\n| Integration | Forced-failure fallback dispatch | New vitest case in `runtime/tests/unit/` |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:testing -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:dependencies -->\n## 6. DEPENDENCIES\n\n| Dependency | Type | Status | Impact if Blocked |\n|------------|------|--------|-------------------|\n| `fallback-router.ts` | Internal | Already shipped, unchanged | N/A |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:dependencies -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:rollback -->\n## 7. ROLLBACK PLAN\n\n- **Trigger**: The new call site introduces a regression in the existing retry path.\n- **Procedure**: Revert the single `fanout-pool.cjs` edit; `fallback-router.ts` and the registry file are additive and harmless to leave in place.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:rollback -->","lineStart":55,"lineEnd":124,"totalLines":124,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/plan.md","time":{"start":1783488809993,"end":1783488809999}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_08ba23be03555888016a4de12972248191a3f325c12c565680"}},"id":"prt_f40378c020019B2oMukKt63Px0","sessionID":"ses_0bfcc9e59ffevWtcj5ONdHm47k","messageID":"msg_f40375b37001fWgcjuYE2uCOoR"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783488810049,"sessionID":"ses_0bfcc9e59ffevWtcj5ONdHm47k","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_p8tIdZ7Mmwpk6STBxo8HKIZR","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/spec.md","offset":95,"limit":35},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n95: | REQ-001 | 3 model lineages dispatched exactly as specified | 10x `openai/gpt-5.5-fast` (`reasoningEffort: xhigh`), 5x `zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2` (`reasoningEffort: max`), 5x `claude-sonnet-5` (`reasoningEffort: xhigh`) — 20 replicas total, confirmed via `research/fanout-attribution.md` |\n96: | REQ-002 | Convergence floor of >=3 iterations per lineage before any early stop | Satisfied automatically: `antiConvergence.minIterations: 3` is baked into every replica's own isolated config by the existing (unmodified) `deep_research_auto.yaml` `step_create_config`, and fan-out merge only runs after all 20 replicas independently terminate — no cross-lineage early-convergence path exists to violate this |\n97: | REQ-003 | Ranked, evidence-cited synthesis produced | `research/research.md` present with findings, each citing which lineage/replica surfaced it and a concrete file:line or artifact reference |\n98: \n99: ### P1 - Required (complete OR user-approved deferral)\n100: \n101: | ID | Requirement | Acceptance Criteria |\n102: |----|-------------|---------------------|\n103: | REQ-004 | GLM-5.2 failures degrade gracefully, not silently | On `maxRetries` exhaustion for a `glm52-N` replica, `fanout-salvage.cjs` recovers partial output; synthesis notes any lineage that finished with fewer than 5 completed replicas |\n104: | REQ-005 | Sonnet-5 lineage dispatched via `cli-claude-code`, never `kind: native` | Confirmed in the executors payload — `native` fan-out dispatch is hardcoded to `model: opus` in `deep_research_auto.yaml` and would silently produce the wrong model |\n105: <!-- /ANCHOR:requirements -->\n106: \n107: ---\n108: \n109: <!-- ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n110: ## 5. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n111: \n112: - **SC-001**: All 3 lineages reach their per-lineage `minIterations: 3` floor; no lineage terminates with 0 completed replicas.\n113: - **SC-002**: `research/research.md` either confirms child 002/003's staged execution plans as-is, or lists concrete, evidence-backed revisions before those phases start.\n114: - **SC-003**: Any genuinely new risk (beyond what the 3 Plan agents already surfaced) is flagged explicitly, not silently folded into the existing risk list.\n115: <!-- /ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n116: \n117: ---\n118: \n119: <!-- ANCHOR:risks -->\n120: ## 6. RISKS & DEPENDENCIES\n121: \n122: | Type | Item | Impact | Mitigation |\n123: |------|------|--------|------------|\n124: | Risk | GLM-5.2 has no automatic fallback to MiMo-v2.5-Pro wired at the fan-out level (`fallback-router.ts` has zero callers today) | A `glm52-N` replica that exhausts `maxRetries` degrades to a same-model retry-and-salvage, not an automatic model swap | Accepted for this phase; operator-mediated manual re-dispatch as `mimo-v2.5-pro` is possible post-hoc since `fanout-merge.cjs` just enumerates `lineages/` subdirectories — see plan.md §Fallback |\n125: | Risk | `cli-claude-code` self-invocation concerns (a prior barter-packet attempt failed on packet-state-write, unrelated to self-invocation) | Low — `fanout-run.cjs` dispatches via direct `spawnSync`, not the `cli-claude-code` skill; its env allowlist strips `CLAUDECODE`; its recursion guard checks an internal marker, not env/ancestry | Recommend a `count: 1` smoke-test replica before committing all 5 Sonnet-5 replicas (see plan.md) |\n126: | Dependency | 3 parallel sonnet-5 Plan agents' file:line-grounded design (this session) | This research phase validates/extends that design rather than starting from zero | N/A — design already captured in child 002/003's own spec.md/plan.md |\n127: <!-- /ANCHOR:risks -->\n128: \n129: ---\n\n(Showing lines 95-129 of 135. Use offset=130 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"| REQ-001 | 3 model lineages dispatched exactly as specified | 10x `openai/gpt-5.5-fast` (`reasoningEffort: xhigh`), 5x `zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2` (`reasoningEffort: max`), 5x `claude-sonnet-5` (`reasoningEffort: xhigh`) — 20 replicas total, confirmed via `research/fanout-attribution.md` |\n| REQ-002 | Convergence floor of >=3 iterations per lineage before any early stop | Satisfied automatically: `antiConvergence.minIterations: 3` is baked into every replica's own isolated config by the existing (unmodified) `deep_research_auto.yaml` `step_create_config`, and fan-out merge only runs after all 20 replicas independently terminate — no cross-lineage early-convergence path exists to violate this |\n| REQ-003 | Ranked, evidence-cited synthesis produced | `research/research.md` present with findings, each citing which lineage/replica surfaced it and a concrete file:line or artifact reference |\n\n### P1 - Required (complete OR user-approved deferral)\n\n| ID | Requirement | Acceptance Criteria |\n|----|-------------|---------------------|\n| REQ-004 | GLM-5.2 failures degrade gracefully, not silently | On `maxRetries` exhaustion for a `glm52-N` replica, `fanout-salvage.cjs` recovers partial output; synthesis notes any lineage that finished with fewer than 5 completed replicas |\n| REQ-005 | Sonnet-5 lineage dispatched via `cli-claude-code`, never `kind: native` | Confirmed in the executors payload — `native` fan-out dispatch is hardcoded to `model: opus` in `deep_research_auto.yaml` and would silently produce the wrong model |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:requirements -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n## 5. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n\n- **SC-001**: All 3 lineages reach their per-lineage `minIterations: 3` floor; no lineage terminates with 0 completed replicas.\n- **SC-002**: `research/research.md` either confirms child 002/003's staged execution plans as-is, or lists concrete, evidence-backed revisions before those phases start.\n- **SC-003**: Any genuinely new risk (beyond what the 3 Plan agents already surfaced) is flagged explicitly, not silently folded into the existing risk list.","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/spec.md","text":"| REQ-001 | 3 model lineages dispatched exactly as specified | 10x `openai/gpt-5.5-fast` (`reasoningEffort: xhigh`), 5x `zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2` (`reasoningEffort: max`), 5x `claude-sonnet-5` (`reasoningEffort: xhigh`) — 20 replicas total, confirmed via `research/fanout-attribution.md` |\n| REQ-002 | Convergence floor of >=3 iterations per lineage before any early stop | Satisfied automatically: `antiConvergence.minIterations: 3` is baked into every replica's own isolated config by the existing (unmodified) `deep_research_auto.yaml` `step_create_config`, and fan-out merge only runs after all 20 replicas independently terminate — no cross-lineage early-convergence path exists to violate this |\n| REQ-003 | Ranked, evidence-cited synthesis produced | `research/research.md` present with findings, each citing which lineage/replica surfaced it and a concrete file:line or artifact reference |\n\n### P1 - Required (complete OR user-approved deferral)\n\n| ID | Requirement | Acceptance Criteria |\n|----|-------------|---------------------|\n| REQ-004 | GLM-5.2 failures degrade gracefully, not silently | On `maxRetries` exhaustion for a `glm52-N` replica, `fanout-salvage.cjs` recovers partial output; synthesis notes any lineage that finished with fewer than 5 completed replicas |\n| REQ-005 | Sonnet-5 lineage dispatched via `cli-claude-code`, never `kind: native` | Confirmed in the executors payload — `native` fan-out dispatch is hardcoded to `model: opus` in `deep_research_auto.yaml` and would silently produce the wrong model |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:requirements -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n## 5. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n\n- **SC-001**: All 3 lineages reach their per-lineage `minIterations: 3` floor; no lineage terminates with 0 completed replicas.\n- **SC-002**: `research/research.md` either confirms child 002/003's staged execution plans as-is, or lists concrete, evidence-backed revisions before those phases start.\n- **SC-003**: Any genuinely new risk (beyond what the 3 Plan agents already surfaced) is flagged explicitly, not silently folded into the existing risk list.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:risks -->\n## 6. RISKS & DEPENDENCIES\n\n| Type | Item | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|------|--------|------------|\n| Risk | GLM-5.2 has no automatic fallback to MiMo-v2.5-Pro wired at the fan-out level (`fallback-router.ts` has zero callers today) | A `glm52-N` replica that exhausts `maxRetries` degrades to a same-model retry-and-salvage, not an automatic model swap | Accepted for this phase; operator-mediated manual re-dispatch as `mimo-v2.5-pro` is possible post-hoc since `fanout-merge.cjs` just enumerates `lineages/` subdirectories — see plan.md §Fallback |\n| Risk | `cli-claude-code` self-invocation concerns (a prior barter-packet attempt failed on packet-state-write, unrelated to self-invocation) | Low — `fanout-run.cjs` dispatches via direct `spawnSync`, not the `cli-claude-code` skill; its env allowlist strips `CLAUDECODE`; its recursion guard checks an internal marker, not env/ancestry | Recommend a `count: 1` smoke-test replica before committing all 5 Sonnet-5 replicas (see plan.md) |\n| Dependency | 3 parallel sonnet-5 Plan agents' file:line-grounded design (this session) | This research phase validates/extends that design rather than starting from zero | N/A — design already captured in child 002/003's own spec.md/plan.md |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:risks -->\n\n---","lineStart":95,"lineEnd":129,"totalLines":135,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/spec.md","time":{"start":1783488810042,"end":1783488810048}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_08ba23be03555888016a4de129722c8191a5a862868cda1b96"}},"id":"prt_f40378c0a001P2YkGP7WVvS09b","sessionID":"ses_0bfcc9e59ffevWtcj5ONdHm47k","messageID":"msg_f40375b37001fWgcjuYE2uCOoR"}}
