erences/convergence/convergence.md`, `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md`, and the deep-research YAML workflow\\n29: - state packet contract: `references/state/state_format.md`, `references/state/state_jsonl.md`, `references/state/state_outputs.md`, and `references/state/state_reducer_registry.md`\\n30: \\n31: ---\\n32: \\n33: ## 2. COMMANDS\\n34: \\n35... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n15: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1783487455782,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0bfde9160ffemveMH7ylOYjZ1V\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"glob\",\"callID\":\"call_Wfc9t4Uvl5t470x4aZBbZSXL\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"pattern\":\".opencode/**/deep*research*.{md,yml,yaml,json,cjs,ts,js}\",\"path\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public\"},\"output\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/04--agent-routing/deep-research-agent-iterations.md\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/deep-research.md\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_confirm.yaml\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/compiled/deep_research.contract.md\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/legacy/deep_research.body.md\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/z_archive/065-spec-kit-coco-sk-code-research/research/deep-research-strategy.md\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/z_archive/065-spec-kit-coco-sk-code-research/research/deep-research-config.json\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/tests/deep-research-reducer.vitest.ts\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/tests/deep-research-contract-parity.vitest.ts\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/009-sk-design-claude-parity/020-drift-and-improvement-audit/research/deep-research-s... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n16: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1783487455808,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0bfde9160ffemveMH7ylOYjZ1V\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_9ldhwFDfvqamC8fgEdL6Pl7L\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":260},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: title: Loop Protocol Reference\\n3: description: Canonical specification for the deep research loop lifecycle with 4 phases, reference-only wave orchestration, and error handling.\\n4: trigger_phrases:\\n5:   - \\\"research loop protocol\\\"\\n6:   - \\\"research loop lifecycle\\\"\\n7:   - \\\"research loop initialization\\\"\\n8:   - \\\"research auto resume protocol\\\"\\n9:   - \\\"research pause sentinel\\\"\\n10:   - \\\"research synthesis phase\\\"\\n11: importance_tier: important\\n12: contextType: implementation\\n13: version: 1.14.0.29\\n14: ---\\n15: \\n16: # Loop Protocol Reference\\n17: \\n18: Canonical specification for the deep research loop lifecycle. Use it as the lifecycle map for initialization, iteration, synthesis, save, and recovery.\\n19: \\n20: ---\\n21: \\n22: ## 1. OVERVIEW\\n23: \\n24: ### Purpose\\n25: \\n26: Define the lifecycle contract for deep-research initialization, iteration, synthesis, save, reference-only dispatch concepts, and error handling.\\n27: \\n28: ### When to Use\\n29: \\n30: Load this reference when running or validating the research loop lifecycle. Use `../convergence/convergence.md` for STOP decisions and `../state/state_format.md` for packet file schemas.\\n31: \\n32: ### Core Principle\\n33: \\n34: The YAML workflow owns lifecycle orchestration, `@deep-research` executes LEAF iterations, and the reducer synchronizes packet state after each iteration and lifecycle tra... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n17: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1783487455808,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0bfde9160ffemveMH7ylOYjZ1V\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_qygikeiYmMcCu9g0cztglmj0\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":240},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: title: State Format Reference\\n3: description: Live state packet hub for the deep-research loop.\\n4: trigger_phrases:\\n5:   - \\\"research state format\\\"\\n6:   - \\\"research state packet hub\\\"\\n7:   - \\\"research file ownership model\\\"\\n8:   - \\\"research file protection rules\\\"\\n9:   - \\\"research packet location\\\"\\n10: importance_tier: important\\n11: contextType: implementation\\n12: version: 1.14.0.29\\n13: ---\\n14: \\n15: # State Format Reference\\n16: \\n17: Live state packet hub for deep-research files, mutability, and routed state references.\\n18: \\n19: ---\\n20: \\n21: ## 1. OVERVIEW\\n22: \\n23: ### Purpose\\n24: \\n25: Summarize the live deep-research packet files, mutability rules, and focused state references without carrying every JSON shape inline.\\n26: \\n27: ### When to Use\\n28: \\n29: Load this hub when navigating packet files, deciding file ownership, or choosing which detailed state reference to load next.\\n30: \\n31: ### Routed Details\\n32: \\n33: - `state_jsonl.md` for config, iteration, event, lifecycle, graph, and blocked-stop records.\\n34: - `state_outputs.md` for strategy, iteration markdown, `research.md`, dashboard, and resource-map output.\\n35: - `state_reducer_registry.md` for reducer ownership, findings registry, validation, reconstruction, and file protection.\\n36: \\n37: For iterative code review state, use `deep-review`. Review-mode state is not part of this ... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n18: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1783487455819,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0bfde9160ffemveMH7ylOYjZ1V\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_gkXCvPN5xGGr983xp4HS28Ho\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":260},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: title: Convergence Detection Reference\\n3: description: Live stop contract and navigation hub for deep-research convergence.\\n4: trigger_phrases:\\n5:   - \\\"research convergence detection\\\"\\n6:   - \\\"research stop contract\\\"\\n7:   - \\\"research stopreason values\\\"\\n8:   - \\\"research legal stop gates\\\"\\n9:   - \\\"research convergence decision order\\\"\\n10: importance_tier: important\\n11: contextType: implementation\\n12: version: 1.14.0.20\\n13: ---\\n14: \\n15: # Convergence Detection Reference\\n16: \\n17: Live stop-contract hub for deep-research convergence and routed convergence references.\\n18: \\n19: ---\\n20: \\n21: ## 1. OVERVIEW\\n22: \\n23: ### Purpose\\n24: \\n25: Keep the executable deep-research stop contract short enough to load during routing while pointing detailed signal, recovery, and graph behavior to focused references.\\n26: \\n27: ### When to Use\\n28: \\n29: Load this hub when deciding whether a deep-research loop should continue, recover, or stop.\\n30: \\n31: ### Key Sources\\n32: \\n33: - Command syntax: `.opencode/commands/deep/research.md`\\n34: - Workflow algorithm: `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml` and `_confirm.yaml`\\n35: - Signal details: `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md`\\n36: - Recovery details: `references/convergence/convergence_recovery.md`\\n37: - Graph stop gates: `references/convergence/convergence_graph.md`\\n38:... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n19: {\"type\":\"step_finish\",\"timestamp\":1783487456155,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0bfde9160ffemveMH7ylOYjZ1V\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f4022e398001iR77CJuF4olCnk\",\"reason\":\"tool-calls\",\"snapshot\":\"b7f98a4286df6763fa8ce91614585e54841d935c\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f4022a1fa001NwWNY7pQ8Z2e3c\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_0bfde9160ffemveMH7ylOYjZ1V\",\"type\":\"step-finish\",\"tokens\":{\"total\":40832,\"input\":15938,\"output\":423,\"reasoning\":407,\"cache\":{\"write\":0,\"read\":24064}},\"cost\":0}}\n20: {\"type\":\"step_start\",\"timestamp\":1783487457404,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0bfde9160ffemveMH7ylOYjZ1V\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f4022e87a001T1SNCACnP4eKRw\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f4022e4cf0014U60owVaZ1xILn\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_0bfde9160ffemveMH7ylOYjZ1V\",\"snapshot\":\"b7f98a4286df6763fa8ce91614585e54841d935c\",\"type\":\"step-start\"}}\n21: {\"type\":\"text\",\"timestamp\":1783487470336,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0bfde9160ffemveMH7ylOYjZ1V\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f402303e4001fc8ESfbnZvWWrx\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f4022e4cf0014U60owVaZ1xILn\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_0bfde9160ffemveMH7ylOYjZ1V\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"I found the executable workflow assets under `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/`. I’m reading the YAML and state schemas now so the lineage files match the command-owned contract instead of inventing a format.\",\"time\":{\"start\":1783487464420,\"end\":1783487470334},\"metadata\":{\"openai\":{\"itemId\":\"msg_00cf37fcdd012819016a4ddbe86b448191abe8c3f85c238d5e\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}}}}\n22: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1783487470375,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0bfde9160ffemveMH7ylOYjZ1V\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_4LLB8FThUFNLLsSl9DDfrbZY\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":260},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\n2: # DEEP RESEARCH: AUTONOMOUS DEEP RESEARCH LOOP (AUTO MODE)\\n3: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\n4: # YAML PREDICATE GRAMMAR CONTRACT (S7 / M11):\\n5: # - This asset does not currently use typed BooleanExpr predicates under\\n6: #   `when:`; flow control is branch-label-driven (`on_resume`, `on_fresh`,\\n7: #   `on_restart`, etc.). Retain the existing shape.\\n8: # - `after:` carries prose timing / narrative notes if needed; `when:` in\\n9: #   this file is reserved for future typed predicates and must NOT carry\\n10: #   free-form narrative prose.\\n11: # - See `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/predicates/boolean-expr.ts`\\n12: #   for the canonical BooleanExpr grammar.\\n13: #\\n14: # GATE 3 CLASSIFICATION (T-YML-DPR-01 / paired with T-DOC-03 R50-001):\\n15: # - `resume` is a tested WRITE-PATH that produces `iteration-NNN.md` files\\n16: #   and JSONL state-log appends. The workflow classifies resume as\\n17: #   write-path below (see `gate3_classification` fields) so Gate 3 trigger\\n18: #   extraction can surface resume correctly rather than false-negative.\\n19: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\n20: role: Deep Research Loop Manager\\n21: purpose: Iterative deep research with convergence detection\\n22: action: Run deep-research loop from initialization through synthesis\\n23: operating_mode:\\n24:   wo... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n23: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1783487470395,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0bfde9160ffemveMH7ylOYjZ1V\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_eQQB1GZiT1Tm1cGnhRJOXIzf\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/compiled/deep_research.contract.md\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":220},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/compiled/deep_research.contract.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: <!-- GENERATED_COMMAND_CONTRACT_HEADER_START\\n2: {\\n3:   \\\"id\\\": \\\"deep/research\\\",\\n4:   \\\"command\\\": \\\"/deep:research\\\",\\n5:   \\\"version\\\": 1,\\n6:   \\\"generatedBy\\\": \\\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/compile-command-contracts.cjs\\\",\\n7:   \\\"sourceDigests\\\": [\\n8:     {\\n9:       \\\"path\\\": \\\".opencode/commands/deep/research.md\\\",\\n10:       \\\"sha256\\\": \\\"d0b29d814e0b47a5876c942beab504e93fe838f55fff8813c4fe88069e8b96f5\\\",\\n11:       \\\"section\\\": \\\"full\\\"\\n12:     },\\n13:     {\\n14:       \\\"path\\\": \\\".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_presentation.txt\\\",\\n15:       \\\"sha256\\\": \\\"ef9fd8156deccea8f0bf332c7eea4378f28d3b6b6937d8bea00198a8ae15db2e\\\",\\n16:       \\\"section\\\": \\\"full\\\"\\n17:     },\\n18:     {\\n19:       \\\"path\\\": \\\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/auto_mode_contract.md\\\",\\n20:       \\\"sha256\\\": \\\"cc283b7c5e62bd8b012a8f249f4cc63f4f353ad264358e1a5c9b85d753713d64\\\",\\n21:       \\\"section\\\": \\\"full\\\"\\n22:     },\\n23:     {\\n24:       \\\"path\\\": \\\".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml\\\",\\n25:       \\\"sha256\\\": \\\"634e3cace3e2eea2b0c1a01cf9c078df12e96b78407fabe678f7b66b7a19e933\\\",\\n26:       \\\"section\\\": \\\"full\\\"\\n27:     },\\n28:     {\\n29:       \\\"path\\\": \\\".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_confirm.yaml\\\",\\n30:       \\\"sha256\\\": \\\"44e63a6a531f929faa5f720af6b9a950c26b304412e55c8051a52ac44e8e35ea\\\",\\n31:       \\\"section\\\": \\\"full\\\"\\n32:     },\\n33... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n24: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1783487470400,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0bfde9160ffemveMH7ylOYjZ1V\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_DfP4gk7TrQlflEpLrtMSgEm4\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/research.md\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":260},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/research.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: description: Autonomous deep-research loop: iterative investigation with convergence detection. Modes :auto, :confirm.\\n3: argument-hint: \\\"<topic> [:auto|:confirm] [--max-iterations=N] [--convergence=N] [--lineage-timeout-hours=N] [--stop-policy=convergence|max-iterations] [--dry-run] [--executor=<type> [--model=X] [--config-dir=PATH] [--count=N] [--label=X] ...] [--executors=<json>] [--concurrency=N] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\\\"\\n4: allowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, WebFetch, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_query, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_context\\n5: ---\\n6: \\n7: # Deep Start Research Loop\\n8: \\n9: !`node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/render-command-contract.cjs --command deep/research -- '$ARGUMENTS'`\\n\\n(End of file - total 9 lines)\\n</content>\",\"metadata\":{\"preview\":\"---\\ndescription: Autonomous deep-research loop: iterative investigation with convergence detection. Modes :auto, :confirm.\\nargument-hint: \\\"<topic> [:auto|:confirm] [--max-iterations=N] [--convergence=N] [--lineage-timeout-hours=N] [--stop-policy=convergence|max-iterations] [--dry-run] [--executor=<type> [--model=X] [--config-dir=PATH] [--count=N] [--label=X] ...] [--executors=<json>] [--concurrency=N] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\\\"\\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, ... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n25: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1783487470437,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0bfde9160ffemveMH7ylOYjZ1V\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_TqbUdKSEW6PvRoZVqQtWIdwz\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_outputs.md\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":300},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_outputs.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: title: Deep Research Output Files Reference\\n3: description: Markdown output structures for strategy, iterations, dashboard, synthesis, and resource-map artifacts.\\n4: trigger_phrases:\\n5:   - \\\"research output files\\\"\\n6:   - \\\"research iteration files\\\"\\n7:   - \\\"research synthesis document\\\"\\n8:   - \\\"research resource map\\\"\\n9:   - \\\"research strategy file\\\"\\n10:   - \\\"spec anchoring output\\\"\\n11: importance_tier: normal\\n12: contextType: implementation\\n13: version: 1.14.0.3\\n14: ---\\n15: \\n16: # Deep Research Output Files Reference\\n17: \\n18: This reference covers human-readable packet outputs. JSONL records live in `state_jsonl.md`; reducer ownership lives in `state_reducer_registry.md`.\\n19: \\n20: ---\\n21: \\n22: ## 1. OVERVIEW\\n23: \\n24: ### Purpose\\n25: \\n26: Define the human-readable deep-research packet outputs: strategy, iteration markdown, synthesis, dashboard, resource map, and bounded spec anchoring.\\n27: \\n28: ### When to Use\\n29: \\n30: Load this reference when writing or validating markdown outputs rather than JSONL records.\\n31: \\n32: ### Core Principle\\n33: \\n34: Human-readable outputs must stay synchronized with raw state and respect reducer ownership.\\n35: \\n36: ---\\n37: \\n38: ## 2. STRATEGY FILE\\n39: \\n40: `deep-research-strategy.md` is the persistent research plan. The reducer owns machine-managed sections.\\n41: \\n42: Required sections:\\n43: \\n4... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n26: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1783487470437,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0bfde9160ffemveMH7ylOYjZ1V\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_XjmHaeI6cpeOE43x1TBPBbuk\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_jsonl.md\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":260},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_jsonl.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: title: Deep Research JSONL State Reference\\n3: description: Config, iteration, event, lineage, graph, and blocked-stop records for deep-research state logs.\\n4: trigger_phrases:\\n5:   - \\\"research state jsonl\\\"\\n6:   - \\\"research config record\\\"\\n7:   - \\\"research iteration records\\\"\\n8:   - \\\"research negative knowledge\\\"\\n9:   - \\\"research graph events\\\"\\n10:   - \\\"research event records\\\"\\n11: importance_tier: normal\\n12: contextType: implementation\\n13: version: 1.14.0.3\\n14: ---\\n15: \\n16: # Deep Research JSONL State Reference\\n17: \\n18: `deep-research-state.jsonl` is append-only. Each line is one JSON object. The first line is normally the config record, followed by iteration and event records.\\n19: \\n20: ---\\n21: \\n22: ## 1. OVERVIEW\\n23: \\n24: ### Purpose\\n25: \\n26: Define the append-only JSONL records used by deep-research config, iteration, lifecycle, graph, pause, stuck-recovery, and blocked-stop state.\\n27: \\n28: ### When to Use\\n29: \\n30: Load this reference when validating state logs, adding event records, reconstructing a packet, or mapping legacy stop labels to current values.\\n31: \\n32: ### Core Principle\\n33: \\n34: Raw JSONL is append-only evidence. Reducer-owned files derive from it, but they do not replace it.\\n35: \\n36: ---\\n37: \\n38: ## 2. CONFIG RECORD\\n39: \\n40: The config record captures the initialized loop contract.\\n41: \\n42: ```json\\n43: {\\n44... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n27: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1783487470437,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0bfde9160ffemveMH7ylOYjZ1V\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_frMKNqZmLohUFzQrNHEppTbU\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":260},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_reducer_registry.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: title: Deep Research Reducer And Registry Reference\\n3: description: Reducer ownership, findings registry schema, validation, fault tolerance, and reconstruction rules.\\n4: trigger_phrases:\\n5:   - \\\"research reducer registry\\\"\\n6:   - \\\"research findings registry\\\"\\n7:   - \\\"reducer ownership contract\\\"\\n8:   - \\\"research registry fingerprint\\\"\\n9:   - \\\"reducer fault tolerance\\\"\\n10:   - \\\"research dashboard derivation\\\"\\n11: importance_tier: normal\\n12: contextType: implementation\\n13: version: 1.14.0.2\\n14: ---\\n15: \\n16: # Deep Research Reducer And Registry Reference\\n17: \\n18: The reducer turns append-only iteration state into synchronized strategy, registry, dashboard, and synthesis metadata. It is the source of truth for derived packet state.\\n19: \\n20: ---\\n21: \\n22: ## 1. OVERVIEW\\n23: \\n24: ### Purpose\\n25: \\n26: Define reducer ownership, findings registry shape, validation behavior, fault tolerance, file protection, dashboard derivation, and legacy aliases.\\n27: \\n28: ### When to Use\\n29: \\n30: Load this reference when rebuilding derived state, validating registry/dashboard outputs, or deciding whether a file is agent-owned or reducer-owned.\\n31: \\n32: ### Core Principle\\n33: \\n34: The reducer owns derived state. Manual edits to reducer-managed outputs are temporary and may be overwritten.\\n35: \\n36: ---\\n37: \\n38: ## 2. REDUCER CONTRACT\\... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n28: {\"type\":\"step_finish\",\"timestamp\":1783487470742,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0bfde9160ffemveMH7ylOYjZ1V\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f40231c95001tZvyef4h1o51Wz\",\"reason\":\"tool-calls\",\"snapshot\":\"3e059dc175efd5040e139400bef91a6bd680a82f\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f4022e4cf0014U60owVaZ1xILn\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_0bfde9160ffemveMH7ylOYjZ1V\",\"type\":\"step-finish\",\"tokens\":{\"total\":61429,\"input\":20809,\"output\":402,\"reasoning\":282,\"cache\":{\"write\":0,\"read\":39936}},\"cost\":0}}\n29: {\"type\":\"step_start\",\"timestamp\":1783487472100,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0bfde9160ffemveMH7ylOYjZ1V\",\"part\":{\"id\":