":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":260},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: title: Loop Protocol Reference\\n3: description: Canonical specification for the deep research loop lifecycle with 4 phases, reference-only wave orchestration, and error handling.\\n4: trigger_phrases:\\n5:   - \\\"research loop protocol\\\"\\n6:   - \\\"research loop lifecycle\\\"\\n7:   - \\\"research loop initialization\\\"\\n8:   - \\\"research auto resume protocol\\\"\\n9:   - \\\"research pause sentinel\\\"\\n10:   - \\\"research synthesis phase\\\"\\n11: importance_tier: important\\n12: contextType: implementation\\n13: version: 1.14.0.29\\n14: ---\\n15: \\n16: # Loop Protocol Reference\\n17: \\n18: Canonical specification for the deep research loop lifecycle. Use it as the lifecycle map for initialization, iteration, synthesis, save, and recovery.\\n19: \\n20: ---\\n21: \\n22: ## 1. OVERVIEW\\n23: \\n24: ### Purpose\\n25: \\n26: Define the lifecycle contract for deep-research initialization, iteration, synthesis, save, reference-only dispatch concepts, and error handling.\\n27: \\n28: ### When to Use\\n29: \\n30: Load this reference when running or validating the research loop lifecycle. Use `../convergence/convergence.md` for STOP decisions and `../state/state_format.md` for packet file schemas.\\n31: \\n32: ### Core Principle\\n33: \\n34: The YAML workflow owns lifecycle orchestration, `@deep-research` executes LEAF iterations, and the reducer synchronizes packet state after each iteration and lifecycle tra... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1783487455808,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0bfde9160ffemveMH7ylOYjZ1V\",\"part\":{