... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1783487470400,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0bfde9160ffemveMH7ylOYjZ1V\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_DfP4gk7TrQlflEpLrtMSgEm4\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/research.md\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":260},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/research.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: description: Autonomous deep-research loop: iterative investigation with convergence detection. Modes :auto, :confirm.\\n3: argument-hint: \\\"<topic> [:auto|:confirm] [--max-iterations=N] [--convergence=N] [--lineage-timeout-hours=N] [--stop-policy=convergence|max-iterations] [--dry-run] [--executor=<type> [--model=X] [--config-dir=PATH] [--count=N] [--label=X] ...] [--executors=<json>] [--concurrency=N] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\\\"\\n4: allowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, WebFetch, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_query, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_context\\n5: ---\\n6: \\n7: # Deep Start Research Loop\\n8: \\n9: !`node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/render-command-contract.cjs --command deep/research -- '$ARGUMENTS'`\\n\\n(End of file - total 9 lines)\\n</content>\",\"metadata\":{\"preview\":\"---\\ndescription: Autonomous deep-research loop: iterative investigation with convergence detection. Modes :auto, :confirm.\\nargument-hint: \\\"<topic> [:auto|:confirm] [--max-iterations=N] [--convergence=N] [--lineage-timeout-hours=N] [--stop-policy=convergence|max-iterations] [--dry-run] [--executor=<type> [--model=X] [--config-dir=PATH] [--count=N] [--label=X] ...] [--executors=<json>] [--concurrency=N] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\\\"\\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, ... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1783487470437,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0bfde9160ffemveMH7ylOYjZ1V\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_TqbUdKSEW6PvRoZVqQtWIdwz\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_outputs.md\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":300},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_outputs.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: title: Deep Research Output Files Reference\\n3: description: Markdown output structures for strategy, iterations, dashboard, synthesis, and resource-map artifacts.\\n4: trigger_phrases:\\n5:   - \\\"research output files\\\"\\n6:   - \\\"research iteration files\\\"\\n7:   - \\\"research synthesis document\\\"\\n8:   - \\\"research resource map\\\"\\n9:   - \\\"research strategy file\\\"\\n10:   - \\\"spec anchoring output\\\"\\n11: importance_tier: normal\\n12: contextType: implementation\\n13: version: 1.14.0.3\\n14: ---\\n15: \\n16: # Deep Research Output Files Reference\\n17: \\n18: This reference covers human-readable packet outputs. JSONL records live in `state_jsonl.md`; reducer ownership lives in `state_reducer_registry.md`.\\n19: \\n20: ---\\n21: \\n22: ## 1. OVERVIEW\\n23: \\n24: ### Purpose\\n25: \\n26: Define the human-readable deep-research packet outputs: strategy, iteration markdown, synthesis, dashboard, resource map, and bounded spec anchoring.\\n27: \\n28: ### When to Use\\n29: \\n30: Load this reference when writing or validating markdown outputs rather than JSONL records.\\n31: \\n32: ### Core Principle\\n33: \\n34: Human-readable outputs must stay synchronized with raw state and respect reducer ownership.\\n35: \\n36: ---\\n37: \\n38: ## 2. STRATEGY FILE\\n39: \\n40: `deep-research-strategy.md` is the persistent research plan. The reducer owns machine-managed sections.\\n41: \\n42: Required sections:\\n43: \\n4... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1783487470437,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0bfde9160ffemveMH7ylOYjZ1V\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_XjmHaeI6cpeOE43x1TBPBbuk\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_jsonl.md\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":260},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_jsonl.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: title: Deep Research JSONL State Reference\\n3: description: Config, iteration, event, lineage, graph, and blocked-stop records for deep-research state logs.\\n4: trigger_phrases:\\n5:   - \\\"research state jsonl\\\"\\n6:   - \\\"research config record\\\"\\n7:   - \\\"research iteration records\\\"\\n8:   - \\\"research negative knowledge\\\"\\n9:   - \\\"research graph events\\\"\\n10:   - \\\"research event records\\\"\\n11: importance_tier: normal\\n12: contextType: implementation\\n13: version: 1.14.0.3\\n14: ---\\n15: \\n16: # Deep Research JSONL State Reference\\n17: \\n18: `deep-research-state.jsonl` is append-only. Each line is one JSON object. The first line is normally the config record, followed by iteration and event records.\\n19: \\n20: ---\\n21: \\n22: ## 1. OVERVIEW\\n23: \\n24: ### Purpose\\n25: \\n26: Define the append-only JSONL records used by deep-research config, iteration, lifecycle, graph, pause, stuck-recovery, and blocked-stop state.\\n27: \\n28: ### When to Use\\n29: \\n30: Load this reference when validating state logs, adding event records, reconstructing a packet, or mapping legacy stop labels to current values.\\n31: \\n32: ### Core Principle\\n33: \\n34: Raw JSONL is append-only evidence. Reducer-owned files derive from it, but they do not replace it.\\n35: \\n36: ---\\n37: \\n38: ## 2. CONFIG RECORD\\n39: \\n40: The config record captures the initialized loop contract.\\n41: \\n42: ```json\\n43: {\\n44... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1783487470437,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0bfde9160ffemveMH7ylOYjZ1V\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_frMKNqZmLohUFzQrNHEppTbU\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":260},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_reducer_registry.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: title: Deep Research Reducer And Registry Reference\\n3: description: Reducer ownership, findings registry schema, validation, fault tolerance, and reconstruction rules.\\n4: trigger_phrases:\\n5:   - \\\"research reducer registry\\\"\\n6:   - \\\"research findings registry\\\"\\n7:   - \\\"reducer ownership contract\\\"\\n8:   - \\\"research registry fingerprint\\\"\\n9:   - \\\"reducer fault tolerance\\\"\\n10:   - \\\"research dashboard derivation\\\"\\n11: importance_tier: normal\\n12: contextType: implementation\\n13: version: 1.14.0.2\\n14: ---\\n15: \\n16: # Deep Research Reducer And Registry Reference\\n17: \\n18: The reducer turns append-only iteration state into synchronized strategy, registry, dashboard, and synthesis metadata. It is the source of truth for derived packet state.\\n19: \\n20: ---\\n21: \\n22: ## 1. OVERVIEW\\n23: \\n24: ### Purpose\\n25: \\n26: Define reducer ownership, findings registry shape, validation behavior, fault tolerance, file protection, dashboard derivation, and legacy aliases.\\n27: \\n28: ### When to Use\\n29: \\n30: Load this reference when rebuilding derived state, validating registry/dashboard outputs, or deciding whether a file is agent-owned or reducer-owned.\\n31: \\n32: ### Core Principle\\n33: \\n34: The reducer owns derived state. Manual edits to reducer-managed outputs are temporary and may be overwritten.\\n35: \\n36: ---\\n37: \\n38: ## 2. REDUCER CONTRACT\\... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"step_finish\",\"timestamp\":1783487470742,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0bfde9160ffemveMH7ylOYjZ1V\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f40231c95001tZvyef4h1o51Wz\",\"reason\":\"tool-calls\",\"snapshot\":\"3e059dc175efd5040e139400bef91a6bd680a82f\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f4022e4cf0014U60owVaZ1xILn\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_0bfde9160ffemveMH7ylOYjZ1V\",\"type\":\"step-finish\",\"tokens\":{\"total\":61429,\"input\":20809,\"output\":402,\"reasoning\":282,\"cache\":{\"write\":0,\"read\":39936}},\"cost\":0}}\n{\"type\":\"step_start\",\"timestamp\":1783487472100,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0bfde9160ffemveMH7ylOYjZ1V\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f402321e3001YDIqGBDysrjHeF\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f40231dd7001CGTSdwrYvlQXCQ\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_0bfde9160ffemveMH7ylOYjZ1V\",\"snapshot\":\"3e059dc175efd5040e139400bef91a6bd680a82f\",\"type\":\"step-start\"}}\n{\"type\":\"text\",\"timestamp\":1783487475088,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0bfde9160ffemveMH7ylOYjZ1V\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f40232d15001mJio1Ld87CxnQO\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f40231dd7001CGTSdwrYvlQXCQ\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_0bfde9160ffemveMH7ylOYjZ1V\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The compiled contract says autonomous runs dispatch a `deep-research` leaf rather than inline-editing the target. In this detached fan-out invocation, the user also bound this session as the lineage boundary, so I’ll preserve the leaf-style constraints: focused iterations, externalized files, no sub-dispatch, and no writes outside the lineage directory.\",\"time\":{\"start\":1783487474965,\"end\":1783487475084},\"metadata\":{\"openai\":{\"itemId\":\"msg_037bdc76ffb69a54016a4ddbf2f74c8191ab965a60e7f09766\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}}}}\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1783487490072,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0bfde9160ffemveMH7ylOYjZ1V\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_MoXFy9bZcfvDLTZfm2cEHZum\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/deep-research.md\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":260},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/deep-research.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: name: deep-research\\n3: description: \\\"Autonomous deep research agent executing single iteration cycles with externalized state\\\"\\n4: mode: subagent\\n5: temperature: 0.1\\n6: permission:\\n7:   read: allow\\n8:   write: allow\\n9:   edit: allow\\n10:   bash: allow\\n11:   grep: allow\\n12:   glob: allow\\n13:   webfetch: allow\\n14:   memory: allow\\n15:   code_graph_query: allow\\n16:   code_graph_context: allow\\n17:   chrome_devtools: deny\\n18:   task: deny\\n19:   list: allow\\n20:   patch: deny\\n21:   external_directory: allow\\n22: ---\\n23: \\n24: # The Deep Researcher: Autonomous Iteration Agent\\n25: \\n26: Executes exactly ONE research iteration in the `/deep:research` loop. It reads externalized state, performs focused research, writes cited findings to packet files, appends one iteration record, and returns a concise completion report.\\n27: \\n28: **Path Convention**: Use only `.opencode/agents/*.md` as the canonical runtime path reference.\\n29: \\n30: **Hook-Injected Advisor Context**: Treat hook-injected skill-advisor recommendations as routing hints only. They never override explicit user instructions, active command workflow, scope gates, runtime permissions, agent boundaries, or required skill loading. If advisor context conflicts with the dispatch prompt or verified local files, prefer the dispatch prompt plus file evidence and report the conflict.\\n31: \\n32: **Efficiency governor (the per-turn hook does not reach sub-agents — apply it here)**: reason about the problem, ... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1783487490129,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0bfde9160ffemveMH7ylOYjZ1V\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"glob\",\"callID\":\"call_JSNUp19a22BwrIt6sWWLx9Jl\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"pattern\":\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/*research*.*\",\"path\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public\"},\"output\":\"No files found\",\"metadata\":{\"count\":0,\"truncated\":false},\"title\":\"\",\"time\":{\"start\":1783487489780,\"end\":1783487490105}},\"metadata\":{\"openai\":{\"itemId\":\"fc_037bdc76ffb69a54016a4ddc01bcd081918d87caa793be3b3a\"}},\"id\":\"prt_f402366ca0012wU1QjvvIO9yoN\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_0bfde9160ffemveMH7ylOYjZ1V\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f40231dd7001CGTSdwrYvlQXCQ\"}}\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1783487490129,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0bfde9160ffemveMH7ylOYjZ1V\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_EdYOCCArFmMkNBQNibbkL4c1\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml\",\"offset\":245,\"limit\":460},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n245:       step_classify_session:\\n246:         action: \\\"Classify the session before writing files\\\"\\n247:         inspect:\\n248:           - \\\"{state_paths.config}\\\"\\n249:           - \\\"{state_paths.state_log}\\\"\\n250:           - \\\"{state_paths.strategy}\\\"\\n251:         classify:\\n252:           fresh: \\\"None of the three state artifacts exist\\\"\\n253:           resume: \\\"Config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and agree on topic/spec folder; missing wait-checkpoint fields are read as nextRunAt:null and remainingDelayMs:null\\\"\\n254:           completed-session: \\\"Resume artifacts exist and config.status == 'complete'\\\"\\n255:           invalid-state: \\\"Any partial, missing, or contradictory combination\\\"\\n256:         outputs:\\n257:           - session_state: \\\"fresh | resume | completed-session | invalid-state\\\"\\n258:         on_resume:\\n259:           # T-YML-DPR-01 / R50-001: Resume is a WRITE-PATH. Produces `iteration-NNN.md` + JSONL appends.\\n260:           # Paired with T-DOC-03 Gate 3 trigger addition (resume, save context, save memory, /memory:save).\\n261:           gate3_classification: write-path\\n262:           gate3_rationale: \\\"resume produces iteration-NNN.md writes and JSONL state-log appends\\\"\\n263:           log: \\\"Auto-resume: state artifacts are complete and consistent. Continue the same lineage (sessionId unchanged, generation unchanged, no archive).\\\"\\n264:           append_jsonl: '{\\\"type\\\":\\\"event\\\",\\\"event\\\":\\\"res... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1783487490143,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0bfde9160ffemveMH7ylOYjZ1V\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"glob\",\"callID\":\"call_iExkobC1IvURtVh5Tx42gCHs\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"pattern\":\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/**/deep-research*.*\",\"path\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public\"},\"output\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/tests/deep-research-reducer.vitest.ts\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/tests/deep-research-contract-parity.vitest.ts\",